{room=116,  	title="The Bridge", 	verbose="You have emerged from the tower onto a stone bridge connecting the East and Black Towers. After the cold stone rooms the air smells sweet and pure and so with renewed vigour you examine your surroundings. The Bridge runs north to the Black Tower but there seems to be no entrance there - the bridge simply stops where it meets the wall. South the bridge disappears into the East Tower and over the edge of the bridge to the west you can see the castle courtyard.", 	n="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	s=115, 	e="Going that way could hurt....", 	w="Going that way could hurt....", 	ne="Going that way could hurt....", 	nw="Going that way could hurt....", 	se="Going that way could hurt....", 	sw=118, 	i=115, 	o=115, 	u="Think you\'re a bird?", 	d="Going that way could hurt...."},
{room=117,  	title="You blunder into a sharp spike", 	verbose="You have blundered into a sharp spike which protrudes from the wall at chest height here. It slides easily through your chest and pierces your heart! Your heart cannot tolerate this sort of treatment and limps on for one or two beats before stopping....", 	n="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	w="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
