{room=119,  	title="Bridge between East and West Towers", 	verbose="You are on a bridge connecting the East and West Towers. This bridge is constructed of a strange glassy substance and you can see your own reflection in its surface. To the west a barred door has been battered down by some forgotten hero.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=118, 	w=120, 	ne=118, 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=120, 	o=118, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=120,  	title="Top of West Tower", 	verbose="You are standing in the room at the very top of the West Tower. This place seems to have been used as a prison at one time judging by the rusting manacles which are firmly affixed to the wall. To your east a barred door hangs from its hinges while to your west a brick wall seems to shimmer in and out of view...", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=119, 	w=98, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=98, 	u="You must be bats!", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=121,  	title="Narrow Trail", 	verbose="You are on a narrow north south trail which leads into a dense forest here. The path seems to fade out as it leads into the trees but from somewhere to the south you can hear the roaring of a fast flowing river.", 	n=57, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=122, 	w=350, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw=57, 	se=125, 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=127, 	o=57, 	u="Think you\'re a squirrel?", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=122,  	title="Amongst some tall trees", 	verbose="The trees here are very tall and there is little undergrowth so progress is relatively easy. To the north you can see that the forest stops abruptly at the edge of a steep hill.\nThere is one particularly tall tree that stands out from the rest. On it you can make out a carving that reads \'To Dear Branwell, Gone but not Forgotten\'", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=123, 	w=121, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw=121, 	se=124, 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=127, 	o=121, 	u="Think you\'re a squirrel?", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=123,  	title="Quiet part of forest", 	verbose="This is a very quiet, relaxing part of the forest where nothing but the singing of the birds and the distant roar of a waterfall can be heard. To the east the forest stops at the base of a cliff while to the south it thins out somewhat allowing you to see the sparkle of the river.\nStood in front of you is a large blooming cherry tree.\nThere is a brass plaque on the tree bearing the inscription \'In loving memory of Heloise the Arch-Witch\'", 	n=601, 	s=124, 	e="You walk into something solid.", 	w=122, 	ne="The forest is too dense.", 	nw="The forest is too dense.", 	se=124, 	sw=125, 	i=125, 	o=122, 	u="Think you\'re a squirrel?", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=124,  	title="North Riverbank near Waterfall", 	verbose="The forest stops here on the banks of a fast flowing river. Spray billows from a huge waterfall which seems to almost pour from the sky above a cliff to the east. West you can see more forest and a jetty which protrudes into the river. There is however, one solitary tree on the bank.\nNailed to the trunk is a small wodden plaque on which the following is engraved...\nIn memory of Nongrata, he fought till the very end. Old times will not be forgotten.", 	n=123, 	s="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	e="You walk into something solid.", 	w=125, 	ne=123, 	nw=122, 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw=126, 	i=125, 	o=122, 	u="Think you\'re a squirrel?", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=125,  	title="North bank", 	verbose="You are at the edge of a forest which meets a fast flowing river to your south where there is a fishermans jetty. In all other directions you can see nothing but forest.", 	n=122, 	s=126, 	e=124, 	w=127, 	ne=123, 	nw=121, 	se="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	sw="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	i=127, 	o=121, 	u="Think you\'re a squirrel?", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=126,  	title="Stone jetty", 	verbose="You are on an old stone jetty here where people would come to fish in days of yore. A few mooring posts show that boats used to come here as well.", 	n=125, 	s="You would only fall in and drown.", 	e="You would only fall in and drown.", 	w="You would only fall in and drown.", 	ne=124, 	nw=127, 	se="You would only fall in and drown.", 	sw="You would only fall in and drown.", 	i="You would only fall in and drown.", 	o=125, 	u="Think you\'re a bird?", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=127,  	title="Dense forest", 	verbose="The forest is very thick and almost impenetrable here. However you can probably force your way through it in almost any direction if you really want to except to the south where you can see the river flowing.\nThrough the trees you can just make out a group of what looks like monkeys all gathered around an elderly man. On closer inspection you see that the man is wearing a pointed hat with the words \'Pippin the Arch-Wizard\' embroidered on it.", 	n=121, 	s="You would only fall in and drown.", 	e=125, 	w=128, 	ne=122, 	nw=121, 	se=126, 	sw="You would only fall in and drown.", 	i="You would only fall in and drown.", 	o=121, 	u="Think you\'re a squirrel?", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
