{room=150,  	title="Inside City Entrance", 	verbose="You are standing just inside the entrance of the ruined city. Roads lead off to all sides of you here but you may not get far along them because of the enormous quantities of rubble strewn about. The road to the south seems reasonably clear though and on a partly collapsed building you can see a street sign reading \"Lions St.\"", 	n=142, 	s=151, 	e=158, 	w=180, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	sw="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	i=151, 	o=142, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=151,  	title="Lions St. North", 	verbose="The road is partially blocked with fallen masonry but you can pick your way through without too much difficulty. The road continues both north and south while the entire facade of the building on the west side of the street has collapsed making it impossible to go that way. On the east side of the street a door with a silvery grey lock leads into a jewellers.", 	n=150, 	s=152, 	e=181, 	w="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	ne=158, 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se=163, 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=181, 	o=150, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=152,  	title="Lions St. North", 	verbose="You are standing at a point on Lions Street where Harlequin Avenue forks off to the southwest and Frobars Plaza leads off to the east. Looking south you can see that the street is blocked with rubble but it might be possible to get a little further in that direction.", 	n=151, 	s=153, 	e=163, 	w=306, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw=306, 	i=163, 	o=151, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=153,  	title="Lions St.", 	verbose="An ornate tower has collapsed across the road here making further progress impossible. Although the tower fell from the west side of the street the buildings on the other side seem curiously undamaged, as if they were made from something other than stone and mortar. There are no doors in any of the buildings here so you may only travel north from here.", 	n=152, 	s="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	e="There\'s no entrance there!", 	w="There\'s no entrance there!", 	ne=163, 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=163, 	o=152, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=154,  	title="Lions St.", 	verbose="You are on Lions Street at a point where a magnificent tower adorned with statues of previous kings has collapsed across the road to the north. A door leads into the buildings to the west while to your east LocoMan Drive leads past some strangely undamaged buildings. At the far end you can see a huge cliff which towers into the sky casting a deep shadow across the buildings at its base.", 	n="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	s=155, 	e=169, 	w="There\'s no entrance there!", 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se=174, 	sw=308, 	i=169, 	o=169, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=155,  	title="Junction of Lions St. and Dagwood Drive", 	verbose="Lions Street runs north and south from here with Dagwood drive to the west and a park to the east. The park is unkempt and overgrown with gnarled and distorted trees protruding from the shrubbery here and there.", 	n=154, 	s=156, 	e=174, 	w=308, 	ne=169, 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se=175, 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i=169, 	o=169, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=156,  	title="Lions St. near north end of overgrown park", 	verbose="The block of buildings on the west side of the road has completely collapsed here leaving little more than a mound of rubble. A few flowers grow here and there from the remains removing a little of the sense of desolation whichs hangs over most of the city. To your south Lion Street continues although there are large cracks here and there in its surface while to your east is an overgrown park.", 	n=155, 	s=157, 	e=175, 	w=332, 	ne=174, 	nw=308, 	se=176, 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=157, 	o=155, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=157,  	title="Lions St. South", 	verbose="Lions Street is so badly cracked and pitted here that progress south is impossible, largely because of a particularly gaping crack in the surface more deservingly called a chasm as you cannot see its bottom. It extends east and west from here and the buildings on the west seem to have collapsed into the chasm, leaving just the odd wall standing.", 	n=156, 	s="You pull back smartly in fright...", 	e=176, 	w="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	ne=175, 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se="You pull back smartly in fright...", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=176, 	o=156, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You pull back smartly in fright..."},
{room=158,  	title="Joshua St. West", 	verbose="You are standing on a road between the City entrance to your west and the base of a tall cliff to your east. The road is bounded to the north by a wall which is so high as to be unscalable and to the south by a parade of shops. Most of the shops have been razed to the ground but a shop directly south of you looks promising although the door that leads into it has a formidable looking lock.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s=185, 	e=159, 	w=150, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=185, 	o=150, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=159,  	title="Junction of Joshua St. and Hunters Road", 	verbose="Roads lead east, west and south from here while passage north is prevented by a huge stone wall. The road south is lined with shops but only a couple of these have been left standing by whatever disaster overtook the city.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=160, 	w=158, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=161, 	o=158, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=160,  	title="Joshua Street East", 	verbose="The street you are on leads west to the City entrance and east to the base of a cliff. It is impossible to reach the cliff itself because of a vast quantity of huge boulders which have been shaken from it. These boulders have also demolished most of the buildings on the south side of the street but to your southeast one building seems to survived, which you can enter by a crack in its wall.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	e="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	w=159, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se=189, 	sw=161, 	i=189, 	o=159, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=161,  	title="Hunters Rd.", 	verbose="The street runs north/south here with intersections at both ends. A few buildings are still standing here, notably a grocery store on the west side and a tailors directly opposite it. Just beside the tailors is a doorway with \"Janets Pad\" printed neatly above it. It is not possible to enter though as a sign reading \"0943 - Out of Order\" is hanging there.", 	n=159, 	s=162, 	e=188, 	w=186, 	ne="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=186, 	o=159, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=162,  	title="Junction of Frobars Plaza and Hunters Rd.", 	verbose="You are at a junction strewn with debris and the odd statue, obviously from the tops of the buildings which have survived. It is however possible to walk along any of the streets which lead off to the north, south, east and west.", 	n=161, 	s=167, 	e=164, 	w=163, 	ne="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i=167, 	o=161, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=163,  	title="Frobars Plaza", 	verbose="This is a narrow paved street with the odd tree here and there. At the western end you can see Lions street while east there is an intersection. There is a signpost in the middle of the plaza, though it has been vandalised and the only sign left reads \"Public conveniences\" and points north, while on the south side of the street a sign hangs above a shop reading \"Ambushbug\'s Swords & Steel - Suppliers to Royalty\". A door fitted with an economy sized steel padlock leads into it.", 	n=278, 	s=187, 	e=162, 	w=152, 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se=167, 	sw=153, 	i=187, 	o=152, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=164,  	title="Alchemists Close", 	verbose="You are in a dark, gloomy street close to the base of the cliff on your east. South is the entrance to an apothecary.", 	n="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	s=190, 	e=165, 	w=162, 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw=161, 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw=167, 	i=190, 	o=162, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=165,  	title="Rockerfaller St. South", 	verbose="A north/south road runs along the base of the cliff here though progress south is impossible due to a rockfall. West leads away from the cliff towards the main shopping areas of the city while to the east you can discern what used to be the forbidding mouth of a tunnel which leading into the cliff, but is now blocked by a large pile of rubble.", 	n=166, 	s="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	e="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	w=164, 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=164, 	u=177, 	d="No hole for you to hide in here, mate."},
{room=166,  	title="Rockerfaller St. North", 	verbose="The cliff overhangs a north/south road here giving rise to a sense of oppressiveness as you look at the thousands of tons of rock hanging above your head. A poor shoemakers shop is on the west side of the street, this being a cheaper part of town. On the other side of the road, tucked in at the base of the cliff, is a blue box with a light on top of it. It looks just large enough for you to enter...", 	n="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	s=165, 	e=194, 	w=189, 	ne="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i=194, 	o=165, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=167,  	title="Draziw Alley", 	verbose="This is a short alley which runs north/south. Strangely the building to your west seems unmarked by the collapse of the others around it.", 	n=162, 	s=168, 	e="There\'s no entrance there!", 	w="There\'s no entrance there!", 	ne=164, 	nw=163, 	se=170, 	sw=169, 	i=168, 	o=163, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=168,  	title="Crossroad at LocoMan Drive & Draziw Alley", 	verbose="This is a crossroad with a narrow alleyway leading off to the north and wider streets running in other directions. West is LocoMan Drive and east, towards the base of the cliff, is the road to the entrance of the city mayor\'s mansion. ", 	n=167, 	s=172, 	e=170, 	w=169, 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i=172, 	o=167, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=169,  	title="Locoman Drive", 	verbose="You are on a wide road which runs across the north end of an overgrown park. North is a large building which is completely untouched by the devastation elsewhere as if some powerful force renders it immune to mortal phenomena. Not entirely, though, as someone has managed to paint \"Arnold proofred here\" on its side.", 	n="There\'s no entrance there!", 	s=174, 	e=168, 	w=154, 	ne=167, 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se=172, 	sw=155, 	i=155, 	o=167, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=170,  	title="Road to Mansion", 	verbose="The road leads east to the entrance to the mayor\'s mansion and west to an intersection. Looking south you can see across the gardens to the mayor\'s mansion, a fine building in its day but now somewhat damaged by boulders falling from the cliff which towers above it. On the north side of the road is a solid cage made from bars of Coder metal which is indestructible. This is the prison where Wizards place mortals who offend them...", 	n="There\'s no entrance there!", 	s="There\'s no entrance there!", 	e=171, 	w=168, 	ne="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	nw=167, 	se="Sorry, that area is closed for construction work.", 	sw=172, 	i="Sorry, that area is closed for construction work.", 	o=167, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=171,  	title="Rockfall at Entrance to Mansion grounds.", 	verbose="The cliff has collapsed in spectacular fashion here blocking movement in most directions, although over the boulders to your south you can catch glimpses of the Mayors mansion and its grounds. You should be able to pick a path through the boulders to the west, back towards the city itself.", 	n="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	w=170, 	ne="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=170, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=172,  	title="Mansion Drive", 	verbose="This is a wide road which is relatively debris free as there are no buildings near. A few odd boulders from the cliff have reached this far but they are easy to bypass. To your east are the grounds of the mayor\'s mansion and beyond them the mansion itself. A wild, unkempt park runs along the west side of the road.", 	n=168, 	s=173, 	e="There\'s no entrance there!", 	w=174, 	ne=170, 	nw=169, 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw=175, 	i=170, 	o=168, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=173,  	title="Mansion Drive South", 	verbose="A gaping chasm runs across the road here and continues east as far as the cliff where it seems to peter out. West it runs into the park but you cannot see how far it extends as it winds back and forth and is soon hidden from sight by the undergrowth. The chasm to your south is spanned by a perilous bridge , which looks as if unwary travellers could easily fall from (and die) while trying to cross...", 	n=172, 	s=485, 	e="There\'s no entrance there!", 	w=176, 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw=175, 	se="You pull back smartly in fright...", 	sw="You pull back smartly in fright...", 	i=176, 	o=172, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You pull back smartly in fright..."},
{room=174,  	title="North End of Park", 	verbose="As soon as you enter a grey mist rises from the ground making it impossible to see. This is a Coders mist which prevents mortals from seeing the lack of form and structure in certain parts of the land.", 	n=169, 	s=175, 	e=172, 	w=155, 	ne=168, 	nw=154, 	se=172, 	sw=156, 	i=175, 	o=168, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
