{room=245,  	title="Narrow room west", 	verbose="You find yourself in a long narrow room which continues to the east. On the southern wall of the room and at regular intervals small stone slabs protrude. They appear as though they might have once been used as seats. The archway set in the west wall leads out.", 	n="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	s="You bang your shin on a stone slab.", 	e=246, 	w=244, 	ne="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	nw="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	se="You bang your shin on a stone slab.", 	sw="You bang your shin on a stone slab.", 	i=246, 	o=244, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d="You are standing on solid rock. Very solid."},
{room=246,  	title="Narrow room east", 	verbose="This seems to be the eastern half of the narrow room.  The southern wall is again furnished with primitive stone seats. In the northern wall a gigantic doorway has been set, which you imagine must lead to somewhere very important.  The other half of this room lies to the west.", 	n=247, 	s="You bang your shin on a stone slab.", 	e="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	w=245, 	ne="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	nw="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	se="You bang your shin on a stone slab.", 	sw="You bang your shin on a stone slab.", 	i=247, 	o=245, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d="You are standing on solid rock. Very solid."},
{room=247,  	title="Meeting chamber", 	verbose="You are standing in a perfectly circular room. In contrast with the rest of these caverns the rock walls, floor and roof are perfectly smooth. The main feature of this room is a vast round table surrounded by chairs which seem also to have been formed from the rock of the cliff. You marvel at the ancient power which could have achieved such a feat.  One of the chairs stands a little way out from under the table and seems to be at the head. The sole exit is to the south.", 	n="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	s=246, 	e="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	w="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	ne="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	nw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	se="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	sw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	i="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	o=246, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d="You are standing on solid rock. Very solid."},
{room=248,  	title="Guard room", 	verbose="This tiny place was probably once used by the being which guarded the rest of these caverns. Your nose detects a foul stench and there are scratch marks in the rock walls, two good reasons why you begin to hope that this being has long since departed. The exit is southwest.", 	n="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	s="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	e="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	w="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	ne="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	nw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	se="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	sw=261, 	i="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	o=261, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d="You are standing on solid rock. Very solid."},
{room=249,  	title="Long passage", 	verbose="The north-south passage continues, sloping gently upwards to the north. A drop of water occasionly falls from the roof and splashes on the damp rock floor.", 	n=250, 	s=244, 	e="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	w="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	ne="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	nw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	se="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	sw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	i=250, 	o=244, 	u=250, 	d=244},
{room=250,  	title="End of long passage", 	verbose="You are standing at the end of the main north-south passage.  A flight of crude stone steps lead north, up into darkness, and from that direction issues a faintly damp mist, accompanied by noise such as that made by a powerful waterfall.\nUnknown hands have also carved a ragged archway in the eastern wall.", 	n=252, 	s=249, 	e=251, 	w="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	ne="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	nw="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	se="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	sw="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	i=251, 	o=249, 	u=252, 	d=249},
{room=251,  	title="Map room", 	verbose="This is a spacious cave with a high roof. The main, in fact only, feature of this room is a huge carving covering all four walls. On closer inspection this proves to be a map of the Land. Although the carving is well worn you are able to discern certain features - a castle, a mansion and an expansive city are all clearly visible. You may re-join the long passage by leaving via an archway in the western wall.", 	n="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	s="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	e="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	w=250, 	ne="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	nw="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	se="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	sw="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	i="You inspect the map from close up. Impressive craftsmanship.", 	o=250, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d="You are standing on solid rock. Very solid."},
{room=252,  	title="Precarious ledge", 	verbose="You stand at the top of a flight of steps which lead down to the south.  Heading northwards there is an extremely narrow ledge, which is terrifyingly high up on the eastern wall of the most gigantic cave imaginable. There is a tremendous opening in the cave to the west, over which foaming torrents of water cascade creating a fantastic booming, rushing sound. Daylight shimmers in through the curtain of water, and a fine mist of water droplets hangs in the air, swirling strangely in the air currents.", 	n=253, 	s=250, 	e="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	w="Vertigo overwhelms you and you scramble back from the edge.", 	ne="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	nw="Vertigo overwhelms you and you scramble back from the edge.", 	se="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	sw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	i=253, 	o=250, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d=250},
{room=253,  	title="Precarious ledge behind waterfall", 	verbose="The narrow ledge, finishing a long climb from the south, levels out and turns sharply eastwards, disappearing into a hole in the cave wall. Far across the cave to the west, daylight enters the cave by a ragged, gaping opening, through which can be seen millions of gallons of water cascading downwards. The noise from the torrent is enormous, almost deafening.", 	n="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	s=252, 	e=254, 	w="Vertigo overwhelms you and you scramble back from the edge.", 	ne="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	nw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	se="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	sw="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	i=254, 	o=252, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d=252},
{room=254,  	title="Low cave", 	verbose="Looking out of this low, dank cave (to the west) you note a rocky ledge leading along the walls of a much larger cavern. A small, ragged and narrow archway to the south leads to what appears to be a cave used for storage, while east is a more formed opening through which brilliant light pours...\nPerhaps most surprising of all, a perfectly hexagonal opening to the north leads into an area of glassy rock, glinting in the light reflecting around you.", 	n=781, 	s=260, 	e=255, 	w=253, 	ne="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	nw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	se="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	sw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	i=260, 	o=253, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d="You are standing on solid rock. Very solid."},
{room=255,  	title="Rune room", 	verbose="As soon as you set foot in this cavern you feel purest energy course through your veins. The walls have a vitreous quality and seem to pulsate emitting sudden bursts of dazzling light.  Carved into every possible space on the walls, floor, and roof are strangely mystic runes and markings, which you sense are the source of this great power. In the centre of the floor there has been cut a perfectly round hole from which you feel an even greater energy radiate. There is also an archway to the west.", 	n="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	s="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	e="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	w=254, 	ne="There appears to be a wall in the way.", 	nw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	se="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	sw="The rock isn\'t quite thin enough to be walked through.", 	i=257, 	o=254, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d=257},
