{room=294,  	title="Room numbers", 	verbose="Some useful room numbers:\n10 - Kings Room       116 - Bridge            130 - Sprite\n142 - City Entrance    192 - WizStore          193 - Prison\n195 - Bar              196 - Lounge            197 - Nightclub\n241 - Magic Factory    320 - Church            350 - Magic Woods\n421 - Black Tower      481 - Start of Mansion Area\n541 - Trophy room      575 - Chattrack         721 - Emporium\n781 - Pillars          841 - Info Centre       845 - Mortals news\n- Exit North -", 	n=281, 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	w="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=295,  	title="Immortal Behaviour (1)", 	verbose="An Immortal has a great deal of power within the game and use of that power involves considerable responsibility as well. What you do as an Immortal is largely up to you, but you must not act in a way that disrupts the game, or significantly affects the score of any of the mortal players. For example, you should not MT the LS from one player and give it to another in order to assist one player kill another.\n- More East -", 	n="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e=296, 	w=281, 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=296,  	title="Immortals Behaviour (2)", 	verbose="Neither should you give large quantities of T to any players or RESET the game while there are significant quantities of treasure left - though you will be put under considerable pressure by mortal personas to do just this. You can of course give small gifts to players, and if you like organise riddles or puzzles for the players with the winner get a prize such as the crown.\n- More East -", 	n="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e=297, 	w=295, 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=297,  	title="Immortals Behaviour (3)", 	verbose="If you do tease mortals, it\'s normal to give them some treasure to make up for it - basically you shouldn\'t give treasures to mortals without making them work for it, but it\'s totally acceptable to give out a couple of thousand points of T per RESET as long as you don\'t favour one player more than the others. Generally wizards should ensure that their aura of power and mystique is enhanced by not showing any favouritism, and zapping players who pester them.\n- More East -", 	n="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e=298, 	w=296, 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=298,  	title="Immortals Behaviour (4)", 	verbose="For example, if a player should decide to kick you, throwing them out of the game will remind them of the power you wield. Of course, some players will always try and annoy you and in these cases you should try to avoid slanging matchs - just keep zapping them! The only real rule as an Immortal is that you must not do anything that materially affects a mortals chances of becoming Immortal - breaking this rule may well lead to the loss of your persona.\n- More East -", 	n="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e=299, 	w=297, 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=299,  	title="Immortals Behaviour (5)", 	verbose="Occasionally you may have cause to kill a mortal, for example if a player is abusive and will not desist even after repeated warnings.  In this sort of case a simple ZAP is not enough of a penalty, but before you take action you must be quite sure it is justified, and have sufficient witnesses.\nRemember, an Immortal is held in awe and respected by most mortals - how you act and how players respond to you is entirely up to you.\n- More East", 	n="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e=300, 	w=298, 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o=281, 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=300,  	title="Immortals Behaviour (6)", 	verbose="Addition by Zeon :-\n If i catch any immortal logged on at the same time as one of their killer seconds then it will assumed that the said immortal is abusing his/her powers by helping his/her second The result of which will be an instant blot, no questions There is NO reason for an immortal to be logged on at the same time as another one of their personna\'s\n- OUT for Index area -", 	n=855, 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	w=299, 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o=281, 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=301,  	title="West End of Vood Street.", 	verbose="You are at the west end of a street which is partially blocked by the collapsed ruins of a church. A high wall to the north blocks out most of the light, but you can make out gaps in the rubble to both east and west.", 	n="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	s=320, 	e=180, 	w=302, 	ne="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	nw="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw=302, 	i=320, 	o=180, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=302,  	title="Laddingford Street", 	verbose="This is the north end of a wide, airy street, bounded by the city walls to north and west. To the south the street gently rises into Laddingford Hill while on the east side there is a rather decrepit looking antique shop.", 	n="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	s=303, 	e=321, 	w="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	ne=301, 	nw="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=321, 	o=301, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=303,  	title="Barricade at Laddingford Hill", 	verbose="You are part way up Laddingford Hill which continues to rise to the south of you, and which is flanked by the city wall to the west.  The way south seems to be blocked by a huge barricade, but perhaps you might find a tool to help you get through it in the tool shop which is to your east.", 	n=302, 	s="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	e=322, 	w="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=322, 	o=302, 	u=304, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=304,  	title="Balancing on a barricade", 	verbose="You have scrambled to the top of a barricade which consists of old furniture, wheels, barbed wire and other unidentifiable objects.  Looking south you can a hill sloping away from you, while north is a short stretch of road and another barricade, which looks even larger than the one you are currently on.", 	n=303, 	s=305, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne=303, 	nw=303, 	se=305, 	sw=305, 	i=305, 	o=303, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=305,  	title="Top of Laddingford Hill.", 	verbose="You are at the top of Laddingford hill on a short stretch of road between barricades to the north and south of you. There is a dark doorway to the southeast of you and beside is a small window.  The window is filthy, and has \"Clean me\" written on it.", 	n="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	s="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	e="There\'s no entrance there!", 	w="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	ne="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	nw="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	se=323, 	sw="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	i=323, 	o=304, 	u=304, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=306,  	title="Junction of Harlequin Avenue and Lions Street.", 	verbose="This is a small avenue which leads from Lions Street to the northeast to Lord Dagwood Square to the southwest. It doesn\'t look as if there was much to see here even when the city was intact, and now all there is the burnt out hulk of a timber merchants to the northwest.", 	n="There\'s no entrance there!", 	s="There\'s no entrance there!", 	e="There\'s no entrance there!", 	w="There\'s no entrance there!", 	ne=152, 	nw=325, 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw=307, 	i=325, 	o=152, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=307,  	title="Harlequin Avenue South", 	verbose="You are at the southerly end of Harlequin avenue which leads northeast towards Lions Street. Looking south you have a fine view of Lord Dagwoods square while in all other directions lies rubble, rubble and more rubble.", 	n="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	s=309, 	e="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	w="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	ne=306, 	nw=326, 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw=309, 	i=326, 	o=306, 	u=327, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=308,  	title="Dagwood Drive near Lions Street South", 	verbose="The ground under your feet is littered with broken glass and crockery from a ruined restaurant to your south. So much debris has fallen from the buildings around you that it\'s difficult to see much in other directions, although you can spy a few stunted trees beyond the fallen timber and masonry to your east.", 	n="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	s=330, 	e=155, 	w=309, 	ne=154, 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se=156, 	sw=330, 	i=330, 	o=154, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=309,  	title="Lord Dagwood\'s Square.", 	verbose="You are now in a large square with a very severly damaged ornamental fountain in the centre. A chaotic jumble of debris blocks your view east but you can see roads and shops in most other directions.", 	n=307, 	s=312, 	e=308, 	w=310, 	ne="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i=330, 	o=307, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=310,  	title="Dagwood Drive West", 	verbose="The road here is relatively clear, and slopes gently upwards to the west where you can see a junction with another street running north, a street blocked by a high, wide, barricade. It might be possible to squeeze past the barricade and travel either west or southwest. If neither option appeals, you are limited in choice to the saddlery on the south side of the road or to the road east, which leads towards Lord Dagwood\'s square.", 	n="There\'s no entrance there!", 	s=328, 	e=309, 	w=390, 	ne=307, 	nw="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	se=312, 	sw=311, 	i=328, 	o=309, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=311,  	title="Collapsed Wall on Blackhand Hill.", 	verbose="This is a very grimy street, and its appearance is not helped by a barricade to the north and a collapsed wall to the west. It doesn\'t look as if you can go south either as the road has split apart there, leaving a deep hole. You should be able to get onto Dagwood Drive through a gap in the rubble to the northeast, or perhaps investigate a dingy building to the east.", 	n="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	s="Going that way could hurt....", 	e=329, 	w="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	ne=310, 	nw="Surprisingly, you are unable to walk through the barricade.", 	se="Going that way could hurt....", 	sw="Going that way could hurt....", 	i=329, 	o=310, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=312,  	title="North End of Mocad Lane", 	verbose="The tall buildings on each side of this narrow road seem to funnel the wind along here, and a few sheets of paper blow about aimlessly.  They probably came from the Bookshop on the east side of the street as there is little else here. The lane continues both north and south but the road south looks very treacherous indeed.", 	n=309, 	s=313, 	e="The door is jammed, and cannot be opened.", 	w="There\'s no entrance there!", 	ne=308, 	nw=310, 	se=313, 	sw=313, 	i="The door is jammed, and cannot be opened.", 	o=309, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=313,  	title="Mocad Lane", 	verbose="The road here has partially collapsed, opening gaping cracks in its surface. To the south you can see a major subsidence where the road appears to plunge into a gaping chasm, and as such probably makes moving south a rather foolish idea.", 	n=312, 	s=314, 	e="There\'s no entrance there!", 	w="There\'s no entrance there!", 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i=314, 	o=312, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=314,  	title="Pit at Mocad Lane South", 	verbose="Ignoring all the warnings to the contrary, you have continued along Mocad Lane and fallen into a deep pit, which is filled almost waist deep in a thick brown sludge. The pit continues to the south, but there\'s no way out there. You are well and truely stuck, unless you can convince someone to help get you out.", 	n="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	s=315, 	e="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	w="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	ne="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	nw="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	se="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	sw="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	i="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	o=315, 	u="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	d="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb."},
{room=315,  	title="Pit at Mocad Lane South", 	verbose="You are sliding around at the south end of a deep pit which is full of thick brown sludge. The pit has steep, slippery sides which are too high to climb. You can go a short way north from here, but you still won\'t be able to get out without help.", 	n=314, 	s="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	e="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	w="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	ne="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	nw="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	se="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	sw="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	i="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	o=314, 	u="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb.", 	d="The walls of the pit are too steep to climb."},
