{room=320,  	title="Inside the Church.", 	verbose="Beams of light flare through the remnants of stained glass windows while broken pews litter the stone floor. The altar has fallen, yet still this place has a sense of sanctity and peace about it.  Should you have no need of prayer, however, the way out is to your immediate north.", 	n=301, 	s="That\'s not the way out.", 	e="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	w="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	ne="That\'s not the way out.", 	nw="That\'s not the way out.", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	o=301, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=321,  	title="Inside the Antique Shop.", 	verbose="Although this shop looks very decrepit from the outside, you are pleasantly surprised by the interior, which looks fairly clean and perhaps even cared for. All of the carriable items have long gone however, leaving only a few cast iron fire grates (far too heavy to take with you) and a few worthless curios. The exit is to your west.", 	n="That\'s not the way out.", 	s="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	e="That\'s not the way out.", 	w=302, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	o=302, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=322,  	title="Inside Tool Shop.", 	verbose="This shop has long been stripped of anything useful and there is little of interest here now. There are rows of nails and hooks on just about every surface and you can almost visualise the proprietor pottering around, hanging a spade here, a hammer there, parcelling screws and nails and generally doing the type of thing the owner of such an establishment does. The only exit is a doorway to the west.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="That\'s not the way out.", 	e="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	w=303, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	o=303, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=323,  	title="The Uglies Meeting Room", 	verbose="You have unwittingly stumbled into a dark and noxious room, littered with fouled rags and bedding. Its looks like the sort of place where the Uglies might meet and discuss their next vile escapade. You pause, and wonder whether the barricades in the street outside were build to keep the towns people out, or the Uglies in. Fortunately for you, light filters dimly through a window beside the door to your west, and has scared the Uglies away.", 	n="Ever tried using a door?", 	s="Ever tried using a door?", 	e=324, 	w=305, 	ne="That\'s not the way out.", 	nw=305, 	se=324, 	sw="That\'s not the way out.", 	i=324, 	o=305, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=324,  	title="The Uglies Inner Den", 	verbose="You gag on the foul miasma that rises from rotting food which litters this inner room, and decide not to spend too long in here. There really isn\'t anything that would interest a person like you anyway.  Light filters dimly through a hole in the wall to your west, and that\'s the only exit from this vile room.", 	n="That\'s not the way out.", 	s="That\'s not the way out.", 	e="That\'s not the way out.", 	w=323, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw=323, 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	o=323, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=325,  	title="Burnt out Timber warehouse.", 	verbose="Picking your way through the burnt out timbers you eye what remains of the roof with caution, as it looks likely to cave in at any time.  You get very black and dirty but can\'t really achieve much here, save to ascertain that the warehouse continues to the southwest and can be left through any of a selections of openings in the east wall.", 	n="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	s=307, 	e=306, 	w="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	ne="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	nw="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	se=306, 	sw=326, 	i=326, 	o=306, 	u="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=326,  	title="Burnt out Timber warehouse.", 	verbose="The roof of the warehouse has completely collapsed here, making it neccessary for you to work hard at making progress. The warehouse continues to the northeast and opens onto Harlequin Avenue to both the southeast and east of you.", 	n="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	s=307, 	e=307, 	w="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	ne="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	nw="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	se="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	sw="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=307, 	u="You get covered in charcoal, but make no progress.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=327,  	title="Inside a mound of rubble.", 	verbose="You have scrambled into an opening between two walls, which have collapsed together and formed this space. You have to crouch in here, and discover that the only exit is the way you came in, through a opening over the rubble to your west.", 	n="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	s="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	e="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	w=307, 	ne="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	nw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	se="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	sw="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	i="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	o=307, 	u="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	d=307},
{room=328,  	title="The Saddlery and Harness shop", 	verbose="This shop is totally empty, and the only evidence you have to support your notion that it was a saddlery is a sign which hangs over the door to the north, read \"J Edgar and Sons, Saddlerys. Est \".  Unfortunately the paint has flaked, and you can\'t make out the date, although there isn\'t really any reason why you should want to know it anyway.", 	n=310, 	s="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	e="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	w="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="There\'s no entrance there!", 	o=310, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=329,  	title="Inside Coal Merchants building.", 	verbose="A few stalls line the sides on the building, each with a black coating of grime showing that this is where coal was stored.  Outside you can see a depressingly dirty north/south street that you can get to by going west.", 	n="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	s="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w=311, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=311, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=330,  	title="Inside a ruined Restaurant", 	verbose="You only need to look once to realise there is nothing of interest here. The floor is littered with broken crockery and a few tables still stand forlornly hoping for someone to sit at them. You decide not to, and consider what to do next. Going north does in fact seem be the only possiblity.", 	n=308, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=308, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=331,  	title="In amidst several piles of books.", 	verbose="You have emerged into a large bookshop which is strewn with books from the collapsed bookshelves all around you. The door to the west leads into Mocad Lane, but the tremendous pile of books jammed just inside the doorway should be sufficient to deter you from attempting to leave that way. At the back of the shop a tiny concealed passage leads downwards.", 	n="There are too many books in the way.", 	s="There are too many books in the way.", 	e=335, 	w="There are too many books in the way.", 	ne="There are too many books in the way.", 	nw="There are too many books in the way.", 	se="There are too many books in the way.", 	sw="There are too many books in the way.", 	i="There are too many books in the way.", 	o=335, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d=335},
{room=332,  	title="The Clock and Watchmakers Shop", 	verbose="The floor and workbenches in this shop are strewn with delicate parts of fine clocks and watches along with the tools for maintaining them. A big old grandfather clock leans against one wall, with its wooden panels now sadly tarnished and cracked. The only obvious exits are through two doors, one to the north and one to the east.", 	n=308, 	s="Ever tried using a door?", 	e=156, 	w="There\'s no entrance there!", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw=333, 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=156, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=333,  	title="The Wand Adjustment Area", 	verbose="More parts and strangely wrought tools lie on the workbenches here.  There is a sense of timeless magic hanging in the air, but it doesn\'t seem to have been strong enough to preserve the contents of the room from the effects of time, which has laid a tarnish over all the metal parts scattered about. Hanging curtains line the walls, and through a gap in them to the northeast you can see the main shop.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s=334, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne=332, 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=334, 	o=332, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=334,  	title="Hand and Face Makers Room", 	verbose="A few pots and brushes sit on a table here, along with some stencils apparently used to help paint the face onto clocks. Here and there lie thin slivers of metal, which on closer examination you discover to be the hands of clocks. Tiny symbols and numerals have been daubed on the walls, some roman, some arabic. It\'s rather dark in here, and the corners of the room are in shadow. You don\'t see any exits.", 	n=333, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=333, 	u="You can\'t climb up here.", 	d=335},
{room=335,  	title="Inside a secret passage", 	verbose="This is a short passage which runs roughly east/west, sloping upwards at each end. The walls are bare and the floor is covered in a thick layer of dust which your feet kick up, causing you to sneeze explosively.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=334, 	w=331, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=331, 	o=334, 	u=331, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
