{room=350,  	title="Magic Woods", 	verbose="You have entered an eerily quiet section of forest, where the trees grow slender and tall, light filtering through their leaves and revealing soft mosses growing thickly on the ground. To the east you can make out a narrow trail, while in all other directions you see nothing but trees. ", 	n="The moss grows so thickly you are unable to walk that way.", 	s="The moss grows so thickly you are unable to walk that way.", 	e=121, 	w="The moss grows so thickly you are unable to walk that way.", 	ne="The moss grows so thickly you are unable to walk that way.", 	nw="The moss grows so thickly you are unable to walk that way.", 	se="The moss grows so thickly you are unable to walk that way.", 	sw=351, 	i="The moss grows so thickly you are unable to walk that way.", 	o=121, 	u="The trees are too slender to take your weight.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=351,  	title="Oak Forest", 	verbose="The trees all around here are all oaks, and the ground is littered with acorns the size of your fist. Some of the trees are strangely gnarled, and you note with some interest that a few of the acorns are half eaten - the indentations left by the teeth of whatever ate them look worrying large....", 	n="A giant red squirrel appears in your way..you retreat hastily.", 	s="A giant red squirrel appears in your way..you retreat hastily.", 	e="A giant red squirrel appears in your way..you retreat hastily.", 	w="A giant red squirrel appears in your way..you retreat hastily.", 	ne=350, 	nw=352, 	se="A giant red squirrel appears in your way..you retreat hastily.", 	sw="A giant red squirrel appears in your way..you retreat hastily.", 	i="A giant red squirrel appears in your way..you retreat hastily.", 	o=350, 	u="A big grey squirrel pelts you with acorns, forcing you back.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=352,  	title="Rotting forest", 	verbose="The air smells of rotting wood, and the going is difficult because of the number of fallen trees. Occasionally a dead branch crashes to the ground, but despite the apparent frequency with which trees fall there are still a goodly number standing.", 	n=353, 	s="A tree in your path crashes to the ground, forcing you back.", 	e="A tree in your path crashes to the ground, forcing you back.", 	w="A tree in your path crashes to the ground, forcing you back.", 	ne="A tree in your path crashes to the ground, forcing you back.", 	nw="A tree in your path crashes to the ground, forcing you back.", 	se=351, 	sw="A tree in your path crashes to the ground, forcing you back.", 	i="A tree in your path crashes to the ground, forcing you back.", 	o=351, 	u="The trees are too dead and rotten to be climbable.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=353,  	title="Black Forest", 	verbose="This part of forest is dark and mysterious, populated with tall conifers. The ground underfoot is thick with pine needles, while here and there huge stone monoliths rise from the ground. You can hear a chittering in the trees and occasionally a large gob of some nameless sticky substance drops onto you.", 	n="A stone monolith glides through the trees, barring your way.", 	s=352, 	e="A stone monolith glides through the trees, barring your way.", 	w="A stone monolith glides through the trees, barring your way.", 	ne=354, 	nw="A stone monolith glides through the trees, barring your way.", 	se="A stone monolith glides through the trees, barring your way.", 	sw="A stone monolith glides through the trees, barring your way.", 	i="A stone monolith glides through the trees, barring your way.", 	o=352, 	u="The bark is too slippery for you to be able to climb here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=354,  	title="Overgrown Forest", 	verbose="The forest thins out slightly here, but the going is made much more difficult by the correspondingly thicker undergrowth. In fact it seems impassable, though a huge and incredibly ancient hollow tree has fallen over and crushed the undergrowth to the southwest of you, offering a route out. The tree itself is lying directly to the south, and you could probably walk right through it if you stooped a little.", 	n="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	s=355, 	e="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	w="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	ne="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	nw="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	se="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	sw=353, 	i="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	o=353, 	u="The bark is too slippery for you to be able to climb here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=355,  	title="Inside hollow tree", 	verbose="You are standing (though in a rather stooped fashion) in the hollowed out trunk of an ancient tree. To the north you can see along the trunk and into a slight clearing, thick with brambles and ferns. The trunk continues south towards the root end, but the way out is blocked by a profusion of roots. However, a hole has been cut in the side of the tree through which you could leave, roughly southeast of you stand.", 	n=354, 	s="Only woodpeckers make holes in hollow trees, dummy.", 	e="Only woodpeckers make holes in hollow trees, dummy.", 	w="Only woodpeckers make holes in hollow trees, dummy.", 	ne="Only woodpeckers make holes in hollow trees, dummy.", 	nw="Only woodpeckers make holes in hollow trees, dummy.", 	se=356, 	sw="Only woodpeckers make holes in hollow trees, dummy.", 	i="Only woodpeckers make holes in hollow trees, dummy.", 	o=354, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=356,  	title="Misty Part of Forest", 	verbose="The ground underfoot is rather wet, and the huge trees around you rise from the groundmist making you feel rather small and insignificant.  To the northeast of you is the remains of a huge tree, long fallen and hollowed out by the animals which inhabit the forest. To the east the mist thins and you can see an area of clear, glistening sand which looks rather inviting.", 	n="Something evil lurks in the mist there, slavering crazily...", 	s="Something evil lurks in the mist there, slavering crazily...", 	e=357, 	w="Something evil lurks in the mist there, slavering crazily...", 	ne="Something evil lurks in the mist there, slavering crazily...", 	nw=355, 	se="Something evil lurks in the mist there, slavering crazily...", 	sw="Something evil lurks in the mist there, slavering crazily...", 	i="Something evil lurks in the mist there, slavering crazily...", 	o=355, 	u="The bark is too slippery for you to be able to climb here.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=357,  	title="Sandpit in Forest", 	verbose="This is a roughly circular area of glistening white sand, with none of the profuse vegetation that surrounds it able to find a fertile foothold in its sterile surface. Trees grow densely all around, but are slightly thinner to the east and west.\nExamining the sand more closely reveals two long shallow depressions running across its surface, crossing in the middle to form a figure rather like a large \"X\". Perhaps something valuable has been buried here.", 	n="The trees are too dense. Either dig a hole, or go east.", 	s="The trees are too dense. Either dig a hole, or go east.", 	e=121, 	w=356, 	ne="The trees are too dense. Either dig a hole, or go east.", 	nw="The trees are too dense. Either dig a hole, or go east.", 	se="The trees are too dense. Either dig a hole, or go east.", 	sw="The trees are too dense. Either dig a hole, or go east.", 	i="The trees are too dense. Either dig a hole, or go east.", 	o=121, 	u="Think you\'re a bird?", 	d="If you want to go down, dig a hole!"},
