{room=361,  	title="Small gap in rubble", 	verbose="You have managed to squeeze yourself into a small gap between the pile of rubble and the top of the tunnel. You can barely make out a passage to the east though it seems to be cluttered with fallen rock and doesn\'t look at all safe.\nTo the west you can see a section of the city!", 	n="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	s="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	e=362, 	w=177, 	ne="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	sw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	i=362, 	o=177, 	u="You must be bats!", 	d=362},
{room=362,  	title="Inside dank tunnel", 	verbose="You are in a tight, dank tunnel leading east/west. To the west however the tunnel has collapsed, blocking the way out, and the east route doesn\'t seem at all safe either though it is passable.  From the top of the rubble to the west you can feel a slight breeze blowing.", 	n="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	s="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	e=363, 	w="The rubble is impenetrable.", 	ne="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	sw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	i=363, 	o=361, 	u=361, 	d="Be serious! What do you expect, buried treasure?"},
{room=363,  	title="Tunnel junction", 	verbose="The tunnel splits off into two smaller tunnels here, one leading to the south and the other leading roughly north-east. The north-east route stops after a few feet, however, due to another rockfall.  You can feel a very slight breeze coming from the west.", 	n="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	s=364, 	e="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	w=362, 	ne="You leap back as the ceiling collapses before you!", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	sw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	i=364, 	o=362, 	u="You bash your head on the ceiling...ouch!", 	d="You get on down, but so what?"},
{room=364,  	title="South tunnel", 	verbose="You have to bend quite low to avoid the ceiling here, but even so the uneven flooring causes you to stumble quite frequently and bash your head against the damp rock. You can hear a faint splashing noise to your south.", 	n=363, 	s=365, 	e="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	w="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	ne="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	sw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	i=365, 	o=363, 	u="You bash your head on the ceiling...ouch!", 	d="The floor may be wet but it\'s not deep enough to swim!"},
{room=365,  	title="South tunnel", 	verbose="Bending almost double to fit through the tunnel, you wade through small pools of water, soaking your ankles. The tunnel ceiling is very damp and every now and then a drop of ice cold water slithers down the back of your neck. To the south you can hear a splashing sort of noise.", 	n=364, 	s=366, 	e="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	w="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	ne="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	sw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	i=366, 	o=364, 	u="You bash your head on the ceiling...ouch!", 	d="The floor may be wet but it\'s not deep enough to swim!"},
{room=366,  	title="South tunnel", 	verbose="The ceiling is now so low that you have to crawl on your hands and knees through pools of ice cold water, getting thoroughly soaked and frozen in the process. I don\'t think you could possibly get any colder or wetter without falling into a lake.\nTo the south you can see a large open area from which you can hear a loud splashing noise.", 	n=365, 	s=367, 	e="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	w="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	ne="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	sw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	i=367, 	o=365, 	u="You bash your head on the ceiling...ouch!", 	d="The floor may be wet but it\'s not deep enough to swim!"},
{room=367,  	title="North edge of underground lake", 	verbose="You are standing in a large underground cavern, at the north edge of a vast, dark lake. Looking to the centre of the lake you can see large drops of water constantly falling from the ceiling, making a quite loud splashing sound as they hit. To your north there is a small gap in the wall of the cavern.", 	n=366, 	s=375, 	e=374, 	w=368, 	ne="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="The unexpected shock of ice cold water forces you back.", 	sw="The unexpected shock of ice cold water forces you back.", 	i=374, 	o=366, 	u="You must be bats!", 	d="The floor may be wet but it\'s not deep enough to swim!"},
