{room=390,  	title="Antonius Avenue East", 	verbose="This is a broad tree-lined, leafy avenue leading to the western outskirts of the city. It is in a relatively good state of repair, and its immense proportions remind you of the grandeur of a bygone age. The air is filled with the singing of birds in the trees.", 	n="There\'s no entrance there!", 	s="There\'s no entrance there!", 	e=310, 	w=391, 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i=391, 	o=310, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="The floor is in the way."},
{room=391,  	title="Antonius Avenue", 	verbose="You continue your march along this leafy avenue, leading west out out of the city, but it is apparent that this section of the road has not been maintained to the same standard as the avenue to the east.", 	n="There\'s no entrance there!", 	s="There\'s no entrance there!", 	e=390, 	w=392, 	ne="There\'s no entrance there!", 	nw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	se="There\'s no entrance there!", 	sw="There\'s no entrance there!", 	i=392, 	o=390, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="You get on down, but so what? "},
{room=392,  	title="Antonius Avenue West", 	verbose="You have reached the end of the avenue which is in a bad state of repair, looking as if it has not been maintained for many, many years. Beyond the end of the avenue a small footpath meanders off through the vegetation to the west. No birds sing here, and the very quietness of the place is oppressive.\nTo the south is a large old building resembling a Roman amphitheatre, although there is no visible sign of access to it, the approach is somewhat obscured by undergrowth.", 	n="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	s="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	e=391, 	w=393, 	ne="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	nw="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	se="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	sw="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	i=393, 	o=391, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="You get on down, but so what?"},
{room=393,  	title="Footpath", 	verbose="This is the end of a narrow footpath leading from the east. The path is very overgrown with brambles. Elderberries hang in profusion from large, old trees, and growths of bindweed threaten to strangle all competetion for the meagre soil.", 	n="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	s="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	e=392, 	w="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	ne="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	nw="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	se="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	sw=394, 	i="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	o=392, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="You get on down, but so what?"},
{room=394,  	title="Undergrowth", 	verbose="You have now forced your way through the dense undergrowth and are to the west of the amphitheatre. You are unable to push your way any further around the building and are becoming increasingly worried in case you can\'t find your way out again.  It may be your imagination, but you feel as if you are being watched.", 	n=393, 	s="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	e="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	w="You are forced back by the thick undergrowth.", 	ne="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	nw="The undergrowth is too thick, sorry.", 	se="You are forced back by the thick undergrowth.", 	sw="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	i="The undergrowth makes progress in that direction impossible.", 	o=393, 	u=395, 	d="Do you really wish the earth would swallow you up, then?"},
{room=395,  	title="Elderberry bush", 	verbose="Sitting in the middle of a large elderberry bush you notice a small branch growing towards a hole high up in the wall surrounding the amphitheatre, but it is doubtful if it will take your weight.", 	n="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	s="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	e=397, 	w="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	ne="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	nw="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	se="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	sw="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=394, 	u=396, 	d=394},
{room=396,  	title="Top of Elderberry bush", 	verbose="You are perched precariously at the top of the bush. The branches here are very weak, it can only be a matter of time before they snap and send you hurtling to the ground.", 	n="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	s="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	e="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	w="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	ne="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	nw="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	se="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	sw="The branches don\'t seem at all safe in that direction.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=395, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d=395},
{room=397,  	title="Elderberry branch", 	verbose="You are perched precariously on a slender branch of an elderberry bush, with the main body of the bush to your west. To your east you can see a hole in the wall surrounding the amphitheatre but you probably can\'t quite reach it directly as the branch isn\'t long enough.", 	n=410, 	s=410, 	e="You just can\'t make it to the hole in the wall.", 	w=395, 	ne=410, 	nw=410, 	se=410, 	sw=410, 	i=410, 	o=395, 	u=410, 	d=410},
{room=398,  	title="Hole in Wall", 	verbose="Here you sit in a hole in the wall. The view from this height is particularly splendid (that is if you like looking out over the top of an ancient forest). Dragging your mind back to more immediate problems, you ponder on your best course of action - you may be able to scramble down the east side of the wall or possibly reach the branches of an elderberry bush on the west side.", 	n="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	s="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	e="Going that way could hurt....", 	w="You just can\'t make it to the elderberry bush.", 	ne="Going that way could hurt....", 	nw="Going that way could hurt....", 	se="Going that way could hurt....", 	sw="Going that way could hurt....", 	i=399, 	o="Going that way could hurt....", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d=399},
{room=399,  	title="Dank, fetid Tunnel.", 	verbose="You find yourself stumbling along a muddy, dank, completely dark tunnel, then slip and fall into a mound of something soft. You have no idea what it is, but there is a fetid odour of animals here.  Above you light filters in from a small hole smashed in the tunnel roof, and looking through you can see a wall, also with a hole in it.  It\'s really too dark to see where you are going, but your feet tell you the tunnel slopes down from here.", 	n="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	s="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	e="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	w="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	ne="You blunder into a cold, hard wall.", 	nw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	se="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	sw="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	i="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	o=398, 	u=398, 	d=400},
{room=400,  	title="End of Tunnel", 	verbose="You have arrived at the end of the tunnel. Light filters in through bars set over a doorway to the east, and through the bars you can just make out tiers of seats curving away to either side. Beside the door is a notice and wiping away the dust from it you can just make a few of the letters:\nABA...HOP..AL..E..HO...TER.HER.", 	n="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	s="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	e=401, 	w="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	ne="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	nw="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	se="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	sw="You squash your nose against the wall.", 	i="You don\'t have the ability to walk through walls.", 	o=399, 	u=399, 	d="You scratch madly at the floor but achieve nothing."},
{room=401,  	title="Lordant\'s Arena", 	verbose="The door leading back into the tunnel system has no handle on it from this side, preventing you from leaving the arena. You have been wondering how the lions survive here, but across the arena you notice the bones of previous Adventurers...", 	n="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	s="You cannot escape that way.", 	e=402, 	w="There is no handle to open the door with on this side.", 	ne=403, 	nw="You cannot escape that way.", 	se=404, 	sw="You cannot escape that way.", 	i=402, 	o=403, 	u="The arena walls are unclimbable, unless you have claws.", 	d="You scratch madly at the floor but achieve nothing."},
{room=402,  	title="Centre of Arena", 	verbose="Resisting the urge to scream loudly for help you stand here, your heart pounding so fast you fear for your life from a heart attack, looking fearfully round the arena for signs of lions.", 	n=403, 	s=404, 	e=405, 	w=401, 	ne=406, 	nw="You cannot escape that way.", 	se="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	sw="You cannot escape that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=405, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="You scratch madly at the floor but achieve nothing."},
