{room=421,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You are standing in the very entrance to the Black tower - the air inside (to the east of you) smells of dankness and death, and it seems to pulsate slightly, carrying on it the sound of almost unbearably sweet singing....", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=422, 	w=80, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=422, 	o=80, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=422,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You are in a room whose walls are made of carved blocks of solid, gleaming darkness..light reflects from the walls, and you can see two possible exits - one to the west of you, leading back into the castle and a darker one to the north, from which issues the sound of singing...it evokes strong feelings of nostalgia and melancholy, and possibly a sense of lost music....", 	n=423, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w=421, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=423, 	o=421, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=423,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="As you enter this room you have the sense of enormous space all around, but it\'s too dark to make much out - you can make out a large, dark pool and, half seen in the centre, a rock with a vaguely human shape on it, which would seem to be the source of the singing which fills the room...to the north is an archway, from which the pulsation in the air seems to emanate, and in the opposite direction is an exit leading to another room.", 	n=424, 	s=422, 	e="You would only fall in and drown.", 	w="You blunder into a cold, hard wall.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You blunder into a cold, hard wall.", 	sw="You blunder into a cold, hard wall.", 	i=424, 	o=422, 	u="You must be bats!", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=424,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You find yourself about halfway up a cavernous shaft, at least eight times your height in diameter. A narrow stone ledge runs around the periphery of the shaft at this point, and there are stone blocks projecting from the wall offering a possible path upwards...apart from that the only way out seems to be an archway to your south.  In the centre of the shaft a metal bar as thick as your arm oscillates slowly back and forth...", 	n="Going that way could hurt....", 	s=423, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=423, 	u=425, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=425,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You are clinging precariously to blocks of stone which protrude from the wall of the shaft. More blocks above and below you allow you to move in those directions, and no others. In the centre of the shaft a steel bar oscillates back and forth, though its motion seems less than further down the shaft, where you can see a narrow ledge running around the shaft...below that it\'s too dark to see.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=424, 	u=426, 	d=424},
{room=426,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You have reached the top of the shaft, and are in a circular room with a solid stone floor and ceiling. There are two holes in the floor, one by the wall which leads down into darkness and another in the centre though which a thick steel bar passes. The bar is moving slightly to and fro, and looking up you see the end of it is affixed to a huge pivot in the ceiling. A tiny crack in the south wall lets light in, and through it you can just make out a bridge.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="The gap\'s too small for you to fit through.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=425, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d=425},
{room=427,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You have managed to scramble part way up the walls of the shaft, but the stones end here so you can go no higher, even though you can see a ledge almost within reach above your head. Looking down you feel swept with vertigo, as the shaft seems to go down without end...  However, not far below you, a narrow bridge spans the shaft and seems to offer some safety at least.", 	n=428, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=429, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d=429},
{room=428,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You are in a small niche recessed into the north side of the shaft.  Looking out across the shaft you can see a thick bar sweep slowly back and forth.", 	n="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	s=427, 	e="You blunder into a cold, hard wall.", 	w="You blunder into a cold, hard wall.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=427, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=429,  	title="In the Black tower", 	verbose="You are stood on a narrow stone span that runs east/west across a cavernous shaft. Looking up you can see a huge pendulum with a perfectly spherical bobweight swing majestically to and fro across the shaft, and it disorients you to watch it for too long..not a good idea as the shaft beneath you seems to plunge to infinity. Apart from this, some stone blocks set into the wall offer a path up, and the east end of the bridge leads into a tunnel.", 	n="Going that way could hurt....", 	s="Going that way could hurt....", 	e=430, 	w="The bridge ends at the west wall of the shaft.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=427, 	u=427, 	d="Going that way could hurt...."},
