{room=549,  	title="NULL", 	verbose="You step through the portal and find yourself in an impenetrable, inky blackness. As you walk forward strange echoing sounds fill the air and you feel a sense of timeless, dimensionless wonder.\nSuddenly you find yourself falling...down...down...down...", 	n="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	s="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	e="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	w="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	ne="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	nw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	se="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	sw="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	i="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	o="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	u="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way", 	d="A mysterious force prevents you moving that way"},
{room=550,  	title="Dangerous Ledge", 	verbose="You are on a narrow ledge which protrudes from the castle walls. A ladder leads up and down from here, and you can get back into the castle via an opening to your south. Looking north you can see the castle gardens, ringed by the moat which curves from the east, where you can see the Black tower, around to your west.\nWater trickles from the fountain and into the pond.", 	n="Going that way could hurt....", 	s=64, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=64, 	o=64, 	u=570, 	d=551},
{room=551,  	title="Halfway down Ladder", 	verbose="You are clinging precariously to the rungs of an old iron ladder fixed to the castle by rivets set deep within the walls. The rungs beneath your hands and feet are gritty with rust, but both ascent and descent are possible.", 	n="Going that way could hurt....", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="Going that way could hurt....", 	w="Going that way could hurt....", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=552, 	o=550, 	u=550, 	d=552},
{room=552,  	title="Stone bench in Formal Gardens.", 	verbose="You are at the base of the north castle wall on a stone patio adorned with a large, simple stone bench. A few slender trees grow gracefully amongst the carpet of flowers beneath your feet, and the hedges which surround you to the north and east offer seclusion and peace. To the west you have a fine view across the moat, while to the south is the castle itself.\nAn old iron ladder is fixed to the wall, offering a means of ascent.", 	n=553, 	s="There\'s a whopping great castle in the way!", 	e="The hedges are not for walking through.", 	w="We do NOT allow walking on water here.", 	ne="The hedges are not for walking through.", 	nw="The hedges are not for walking through.", 	se="There\'s a whopping great castle in the way!", 	sw="The hedges are not for walking through.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=551, 	u=551, 	d="Be serious! What do you expect, buried treasure?"},
{room=553,  	title="In the Castle\'s Rose Garden", 	verbose="The hedges surround you on all sides except the west, where the moat passes still, silent and deep. Some untended rose beds in the centre of the garden blossom with gorgeous colours and give off a sweet smell of summers past, and summers yet to come.", 	n="The hedge is imbued with life of its own, and forces you back.", 	s=552, 	e=557, 	w="The moat keeps people in as well as keeping them out.", 	ne="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	nw="The moat keeps people in as well as keeping them out.", 	se=556, 	sw="The moat keeps people in as well as keeping them out.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=552, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="Why, did you bury a bone around here someplace?"},
{room=554,  	title="Overgrown Briar Patch", 	verbose="This part of the garden has grown wild more quickly than the rest, being little more than a briar patch surrounded by wildly overgrown bushs to the east and south. The vegetation grows thickest on the bank of the moat, possibly the seeds were carried in by it. Looking north you can see a big old tree towering above the hedgerow.", 	n=555, 	s="You are scratched badly by the briars and get nowhere.", 	e=558, 	w="We do NOT allow walking on water here.", 	ne="You are scratched badly by the briars and get nowhere.", 	nw="You are scratched badly by the briars and get nowhere.", 	se="You are scratched badly by the briars and get nowhere.", 	sw="You are scratched badly by the briars and get nowhere.", 	i="You are scratched badly by the briars and get nowhere.", 	o=558, 	u="You aren\'t talking to a dog now, you know.", 	d="Do you really wish the earth would swallow you up, then?"},
{room=555,  	title="The Shaded Garden", 	verbose="You are at the north end of the garden, and the moat curves across in front of you, running from the north to the west. The area is totally dominated by a massively ancient tree, which rises high above the hedges to the east and south. Examining it briefly, you decide it was here before the castle was built, and will probably remain long after the castle has crumbled to dust.", 	n="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	s=554, 	e=559, 	w="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	ne="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	nw="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	se="The hedge is imbued with life of its own, and forces you back.", 	sw="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	i="A benevolent tree spirit is already in the tree.", 	o=554, 	u="What, you want me to sit up and beg? Forget it.", 	d="You get on down, but so what?"},
{room=556,  	title="The Miniature Garden", 	verbose="This area of the garden seems to have been a miniature map of the Formal Gardens, complete with tiny trees and an arc of violets obviously meant to represent the moat. Unfortunately the model is choked with grass and wild flowers, rendering it useless as a guide.  To the south the castle towers above you, and there seems to have been an entrance there once, but massive chunks of stone have fallen from the parapets and make investigation impossible.", 	n=557, 	s="The blocks of stone in the way are totally immoveable.", 	e=560, 	w="A hedgehog bites your ankle and you retreat hastily!", 	ne="A hedgehog bites your ankle and you retreat hastily!", 	nw=553, 	se="There\'s a whopping great castle in the way!", 	sw="There\'s a whopping great castle in the way!", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=553, 	u="The castle walls are too steep to be climbable.", 	d="Be serious! What do you expect, buried treasure?"},
{room=557,  	title="Beside the ruins of an old bandstand", 	verbose="Hedges grow tall and silent on all sides of you, at one time surrounding the old bandstand in the centre of this area with a perfect circle of vegetation. Now with the growth that has occurred over the years it\'s difficult to imagine how this place would look if properly tended. But you don\'t really think about that too much, as you scan the hedges looking for a path or another clue as to where an exit might be.", 	n="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	s=556, 	e="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	w=553, 	ne="The hedge rustles and spits a stinging liquid at you!", 	nw="The hedge rustles and spits a stinging liquid at you!", 	se="The hedge rustles and spits a stinging liquid at you!", 	sw="The hedge rustles and spits a stinging liquid at you!", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=553, 	u="What, you want me to sit up and beg? Forget it.", 	d="You get on down, but so what?"},
{room=558,  	title="On the Croquet Lawn", 	verbose="You have emerged from a gap in the hedges to find yourself on what was once a croquet lawn, revealed by the old hoops that protrude from the long grass here and there. Over the hedge to the north you can see the top of some sort of a fountain, and to the west of it a tree.  South can be seen the castle, standing magnificently proud against the sky.", 	n="The hedge is imbued with life of its own, and forces you back.", 	s=557, 	e=562, 	w=554, 	ne=563, 	nw="The hedges are not for walking through.", 	se="The hedges are not for walking through.", 	sw=553, 	i="The hedges are not for walking through.", 	o=557, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="Do you really wish the earth would swallow you up, then?"},
{room=559,  	title="The Fountain in the Formal Gardens", 	verbose="You are at the most northern point in the gardens, evidenced by the moat before you which curves gently from east to west. South you can see the castle, and to the west a tree but the wildly overgrown vegetation makes it difficult to see much else.  A large, still, pond mirrors the sky before you, and rising from the centre is a magnificently decadent statue, obviously the source of a fountain. You couldn\'t describe it to your children without blushing.  Water trickles from the fountain and into the pond.", 	n="We do NOT allow walking on water here.", 	s="A hedgehog bites your ankle and you retreat hastily!", 	e="The hedge is imbued with life of its own, and forces you back.", 	w=555, 	ne="We do NOT allow walking on water here.", 	nw="We do NOT allow walking on water here.", 	se="The hedge is imbued with life of its own, and forces you back.", 	sw="The hedge is imbued with life of its own, and forces you back.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=555, 	u="You aren\'t talking to a dog now, you know.", 	d="Do you really wish the earth would swallow you up, then?"},
{room=560,  	title="Summer house in Formal Gardens", 	verbose="Here, nestled against the castle walls to the south, lie the splintered remains of a white summerhouse, crushed by blocks of masonry and gargoyles toppled from the castle battlements high above you. Looking up, you note that the tower which rises massively above you is darker in colour than the rest of the castle.  To the east of you the moat curves away to the north, and across it you can see a wood and the end of a path, possibly the source of firewood for the castle.", 	n=561, 	s="There\'s a whopping great castle in the way!", 	e="We do NOT allow walking on water here.", 	w=556, 	ne="The moat keeps people in as well as keeping them out.", 	nw="A hedgehog bites your ankle and you retreat hastily!", 	se="There\'s a whopping great castle in the way!", 	sw="There\'s a whopping great castle in the way!", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=556, 	u="The castle walls are too steep to be climbable.", 	d="Why, did you bury a bone around here someplace?"},
{room=561,  	title="By the overgrown orchid beds", 	verbose="The hedges grow on all sides of you, except to the east where you can see a moat, and in it a reflection of a wood on the other side.  Looking at the far bank, you notice a drainage ditch running into the moat, obviously there to keep the water level up.  Orchids grow in wild profusion from untended flowerbeds, and you can still see a few tags in the ground inscribed with exotic names.  Evidently these were once carefully cultivated by some botanical expert.", 	n=562, 	s=560, 	e="We do NOT allow walking on water here.", 	w=557, 	ne="The moat keeps people in as well as keeping them out.", 	nw="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	se="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	sw="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	i="You really should have learnt to swim.", 	o=560, 	u="You flap your arms furiously and rise about a hairs breadth.", 	d="Be serious! What do you expect, buried treasure?"},
{room=562,  	title="Beside the statues of long forgotten heros.", 	verbose="Several statues stand silently on the banks of the moat to the east while in all other directions the hedges obscure your vision. Birds sing sweetly somewhere to the south of you.", 	n=563, 	s=561, 	e="The statues seem to....MOVE....and block your way.", 	w=558, 	ne="The statues seem to....MOVE....and block your way.", 	nw="The statues seem to....MOVE....and block your way.", 	se="The statues seem to....MOVE....and block your way.", 	sw="The statues seem to....MOVE....and block your way.", 	i="The statues seem to....MOVE....and block your way.", 	o=561, 	u="You aren\'t talking to a dog now, you know.", 	d="Do you really wish the earth would swallow you up, then?"},
{room=563,  	title="Inside the Aviary", 	verbose="You have emerged in what appears to have once been an aviary, carefully constructed by joining the tops of the hedges with long, thin poles and skillfully weaving with fine rope. Now, the rope has rotted and although large apertures gape in the roof, some birds have evidently made their home within this sanctuary, their presence only revealed by their singing within the foliage.  To your south the remains of a door, carefully crafted to blend with the surroundings, hangs on one hinge.", 	n="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	s=562, 	e="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	w="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	ne="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	nw="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	se="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	sw="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	i="You can\'t seem to find a way through the hedge.", 	o=562, 	u="Think you\'re a bird?", 	d="Do you really wish the earth would swallow you up, then?"},
