{room=571,  	title="Lookout point behind Castle Parapet", 	verbose="This is a wide ledge, not far below the top of the castle, with a low parapet to the north where a ladder can be seen leading down. The stone floor has been worn smooth by the slow pacing of the lookout guards in days of yore.  Looking north, you can see the Castle Gardens spread before you, encircled by the moat which runs from the west and curves across the north end of the gardens before disappearing behind the castle to the east. At the north end of the gardens can be seen a fountain.\nWater trickles from the fountain and into the pond.", 	n="Going that way could hurt....", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="Going that way could hurt....", 	nw="Going that way could hurt....", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=570, 	u="The next section of ladder is missing.", 	d=570},
