{room=575,  	title="The Post Room", 	verbose="Welcome to the Post Room! This room is the key to the ChatTrack, a circuit of rooms where you can paste messages for all to see and to read messages put up by others. To begin reading, go South to start from the latest message or SouthWest to start from the earliest - once on the ChatTrack use NEXT/F/FORWARD or B/BACK to read the next or previous message, respectively.\nGo West to find out how to post a message, or North to get back to the Pan-Dimensional Tunnel.\nOlder messages appear in Inshades", 	n=580, 	s=575, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w=576, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw=575, 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=580, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=576,  	title="Post Room Information (1)", 	verbose="To post your own message on the ChatTrack, use the SUBJECT command first to set the title of the message, for example you might type \"SUBJECT Mercenary for Hire\". Once you\'ve set the subject you can type ADD <Text> to add to the message a line at a time, for example \"ADD Anyone need dirty deeds done cheap? Mail me if so!\". At any point you can type REVIEW to check on your progress so far.\n--- More West ---", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=575, 	w=577, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=577, 	o=575, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=577,  	title="Post Room Information (2)", 	verbose="If you make an error you can either restart by using the SUBJECT command again, or you can use one of the DELETE options - to get a list of these type \"DELETE ?\". You can also insert lines with the INSERT command - to insert a new line type INSERT n <Text>, for example INSERT 2 This was Inserted!  would insert the text as line 2.\n--- More West ---", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=576, 	w=578, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=578, 	o=576, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=578,  	title="Post Room Information (3)", 	verbose="Once you are happy with your message, type POST to post it onto the ChatTrack as the latest message. Going \"OUT\" in a ChatTrack room will move you back to the Post Room. You may use the chattrack to discuss anything at all, but it would preferably be at least faintly related to the game.\n--- East to read back, OUT for Post Room --- ", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=577, 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=575, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=579,  	title="Post Room Information (4) *Reserved*", 	verbose="You\'re stuck in an unused room. What a shame.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=580,  	title="Pan-dimensional Tunnel", 	verbose="You are in a dark tunnel which doesn\'t quite seem to have reality on its side. To the east it opens into a large underground cavern containing a comfortable sprawl of a building made of warm stone, while to the west the tunnel darkens into shadow, and leads to a strange and timeless land of twilight and magic...  The north wall contains a marble portal with a sign above it saying \"FIRE EXIT - KEEP CLEAR\".  In the South Wall is a second portal, marked simply \"Post Room\".", 	n=549, 	s=575, 	e=581, 	w=1, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=581, 	o=1, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=581,  	title="Outside the \"Bag and Brick\" pub", 	verbose="You are at the entrance of the Bag and Brick, an area reserved for peaceful chatting, meeting friends for a drink and generally relaxing while accepting large bribes from certain corrupt officials. To the south is a door labelled \"The Olde Public Bar\", to the east is a dark door labelled \"The Den\" and to the north is a narrow alleyway. Above you hangs a complex scoreboard of some kind, and looking at the walls just makes you cross-eyed.", 	n=584, 	s=582, 	e=583, 	w=580, 	ne=890, 	nw="Ever tried using a door?", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="Ever tried using a door?", 	i=583, 	o=580, 	u=1070, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=582,  	title="Ye Olde Public Bar", 	verbose="This is part of the public area of the Corrupt Mayor, a bar whose floor is covered with spit and sawdust. An old dartboard hangs in one corner, the wall around it gouged by wayward arrers. Several trestle tables cover the main floor area and a few stools line the bar itself.\nThere are doors labelled \"Waye out\",\"The Den\",\"Ye Gentlemen\" and \"Ye Ladies\" heading respectively, northwest, northeast, southeast and southwest.", 	n=581, 	s="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	e="Whoops! Who put that wall there?", 	w="Whoops! Who put that wall there?", 	ne=583, 	nw=581, 	se=593, 	sw=594, 	i=583, 	o=581, 	u="You clamber drunkenly onto the bar and promptly fall off.", 	d="Trying to slide under the table, eh?"},
{room=583,  	title="The Killers Den", 	verbose="You find yourself in a dark, claustrophobic room, with alcoves near the door for visitors to rest their weaponry in, while set into one nearby wall is a screen of dark glass, though which yellow writing glows. Judging from the sword and axe marks on the furniture, and the gouge marks on the walls, this is the sort of place frequented by the more, well, violent, sort of person.  At the west end of the room is a door leads outside, with other doors to north and south.", 	n=585, 	s=582, 	e="Ever tried using a door?", 	w=581, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=585, 	o=581, 	u="You clamber drunkenly onto the bar and promptly fall off.", 	d="Trying to slide under the table, eh?"},
{room=584,  	title="Alleyway", 	verbose="This is a narrow alleyway running from the south, where there is a pub, to the northwest, where steps lead down into a brightly lit area - above the steps hangs a sign reading \"Information\". To the east stands a small hostelry of comfortable appearance.", 	n=841, 	s=581, 	e=585, 	w="You blunder into a cold, hard wall.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw=841, 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=841, 	o=841, 	u="You must be bats!", 	d=841},
{room=585,  	title="Inn Reception", 	verbose="You are in a small foyer just inside the Travellers Rest, a fine inn though of dated appearance. A door to the west is labelled \"Guest lounge\" while to the south another doorway leads into the Den.  Stairs lead up to the north, through your trained perceptions tell you there is some sorcerous spell at work on the staircase.", 	n=589, 	s=583, 	e=586, 	w=584, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=586, 	o=584, 	u=589, 	d="No hole for you to hide in here, mate."},
{room=586,  	title="Inn Lounge", 	verbose="This is one of those rooms you immediately feel at home in, a huge log fire in one corner of the room spreading warmth throughout. A few doors lead off here and there, one west to Reception, one east to a conference room and another south to the Auditorium.", 	n="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	s=588, 	e=587, 	w=585, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=587, 	o=585, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=587,  	title="Conference room", 	verbose="You are in a large room with a round dome in the ceiling and a long teak table dominating the rest of the room. A few chairs are pulled up to the table with others pushed back against the wall.  There is only one door to this room, and that\'s to your west.", 	n="You walk straight into a wall. Ouch.", 	s="That\'s not the way out.", 	e="That\'s not the way out.", 	w=586, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=586, 	u="You climb onto the table, slip, and fall off.", 	d="Trying to slide under the table, eh?"},
{room=588,  	title="Auditorium", 	verbose="You are in a small auditorium, with a slightly raised stage and podium at the south end. Facing it are several rows of chairs, and it\'s obviously a room used for lectures and talks of one kind or another. At the north end of the room is a doorway with a sign above it, reading \"Exit\".", 	n=586, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=586, 	u="You aren\'t allowed on the podium.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
