{room=781,  	title="The Obsidian cave", 	verbose="Light gleams off sharply fractured rock in this larger cave, the walls and ceiling being of dark glassy obsidian. The floor is relatively level though slick with water, forming small pools into which water drips slowly from the ceiling with an almost musical sound.\nDespite the jumble and confusion of shattered rock, you observe exits at both the southern and northern ends.", 	n=782, 	s=254, 	e="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	w="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	ne="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	nw="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	se="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	sw="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	i=782, 	o=254, 	u="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	d="You are standing on solid rock. Very solid."},
{room=782,  	title="Fracture ledge within cave", 	verbose="Behind you, to the south, is a cave full of jagged, vicious looking, glassy obsidian, though this is nothing compared to the scene to the northwest, where the roof of the cavern has collapsed downwards, huge but irregularly shaped splinters of rock creating a formidable barrier.  The floor to the north is clear, but is several feet lower as the floor there has fractured and sunk, creating the small ledge on which you are standing. ", 	n=783, 	s=781, 	e="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=783, 	o=781, 	u="You must be bats!", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=783,  	title="Deep within the Obsidian Cave", 	verbose="The floor here is clear, through blocked by splinters of dark rock fallen from the ceiling to your west and to your south by a ledge which is just slightly too high to be reachable. Letting your eyes follow the cave wall to the east you can make out what appears to be a regular structure of some form, visible where the wall disappears into the darkness to the north.  From that direction comes a complex sound of many tones...", 	n=784, 	s=782, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	ne="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	sw="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	i=784, 	o=782, 	u="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	d="You claw at the solid rock floor and break a fingernail."},
{room=784,  	title="Before the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="South the cave disappears into unrelieved darkness, but here you can see far enough north to determine a regular structure of huge hexagonal pillars, towering towards the roof and formed of darkly crystaline rock. A deep, rich, and enormously complex sequence of varying tones emanates from behind the pillars, or perhaps from within them.  There is an inscription on the wall beside you, and a arrow pointing towards the pillars.", 	n=785, 	s=783, 	e="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	w="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	ne=785, 	nw=783, 	se="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	sw="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	i=785, 	o=783, 	u="The ceiling is far too high for you to reach.", 	d="You claw at the solid rock floor and break a fingernail."},
{room=785,  	title="At the Foot of the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="Standing at the base of one of the pillars, you can feel a vibration emanating from deep with in, echoing away down the cave to the south.  From here you can discern that there are twenty seven pillars in all, forming three equal length east-west rows. The front row, immediately before you, are lower than the middle row which is in turn lower than the back row.  You can reach the top of the most easterly pillar in the front row by a staircase cut into the cave wall to the northeast.", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s=784, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne=786, 	nw="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	se=784, 	sw=784, 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=784, 	u=786, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=786,  	title="On the Obsidian staircase", 	verbose="A few steps from the bottom of a staircase carved from obsidian, you look at the pillars again and observe that each of the rows (still some way above your head) slope - the first row rising from the east to the west, where it becomes almost the height of the lowest pillar in the middle row, which rises in the opposite direction, up to the east. The top row follows the pattern, and on reflection it strikes you that the pillars resemble a gigantic staircase.", 	n=787, 	s=785, 	e="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	nw="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=785, 	u=787, 	d=785},
{room=787,  	title="Halfway up Obsidian staircase", 	verbose="Approximately halfway up (or down, if you prefer) the staircase, you can now appreciate the massive scale of these pillars, which strike you as if they\'ve been almost grown in some gigantic crystal bath.  The sound emanating from them can now be heard all around, and you note each pillar has its own distinct tone, fading in and out of the overall sound pattern.", 	n=788, 	s=786, 	e="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	w="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=786, 	u=788, 	d=786},
{room=788,  	title="Top of the Obsidian staircase.", 	verbose="Here, at the top of the obsidian staircase, you can easily step west onto the wide, flat surface of the most easterly pillar of the front row. Looking along the nine pillars of the first row, you note that although generally the pillars get taller away to the west, there is a repeated pattern in which sets of three pillars rise along the row, then drop slightly to the next set, giving the overall ascent a slightly jagged, serrated, look. Meaningful, you wonder?", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s=787, 	e="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	w=789, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=787, 	u="Sorry. No levitating on these premises.", 	d=787},
{room=789,  	title="East Pillar - Bottom of First Row", 	verbose="You are stood on the shortest of the pillars, and through your feet you can feel a tingling vibration, almost certainly connected with the single, pure tone emanating from the pillar. East is the staircase which provides access to this pillar, while west the pillars rise to meet the lower end of the second row.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n !  I  !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=788, 	w=790, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=788, 	u=790, 	d=788},
{room=790,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="You are stood atop a pillar in the front row, and can step up to the pillar on your west or down to the pillar on your east - the general slope of the pillars is up to the west.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n !  I  !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e=789, 	w=791, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=789, 	u=791, 	d=789},
{room=791,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="You are stood atop a pillar in the front row, and can step down to the pillar on your east or onto the pillar on your west - the pillars generally slope up to the west, even though the next pillar in that direction requires a slight step down.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n !  I  !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=790, 	w=792, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=790, 	u=792, 	d=790},
{room=792,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="You are stood atop the fourth pillar in the front row, and can step up either to the pillar on your west or to the one on your east - the pillars generally slope up to the west, even though the pillars both sides of you are slightly higher than the one you are currently on.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n !  II !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="It\'s a long way down, and you don\'t feel suicidal.", 	e=791, 	w=793, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=791, 	u=793, 	d=791},
{room=793,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="You are stood atop a pillar in the front row, and can step up to the pillar on your west or down to the pillar on your east - the pillars in the second row, to your north, reach above your head.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n !  II !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=792, 	w=794, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=792, 	u=794, 	d=792},
{room=794,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="You are stood atop a pillar in the front row, and can step down to either the pillar on your west or to the one on your east - the pillars generally slope down to the east and up to the west, however.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n !  II !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=793, 	w=795, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=793, 	u=795, 	d=793},
{room=795,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="You are stood atop the seventh pillar in the front row, and can step up to either the pillar on your west or to the one on your east - the pillars generally slope up to the west, even though the pillars both sides of you are slightly higher than the one you are currently on.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n ! III !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="It\'s a long way down, and you don\'t feel suicidal.", 	e=794, 	w=796, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=794, 	u=796, 	d=794},
{room=796,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="The pillars slope down to the east, and to the west there is just one more pillar, where you can easily reach the lowest pillar in the second row by going north there - in fact you can probably scramble onto the second row from here.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n ! III !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=795, 	w=797, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=795, 	u=799, 	d=795},
{room=797,  	title="On the Singing Pillars - Top of First Row", 	verbose="You are stood atop the highest pillar in the first row, and can see the height you have climbed by surveying the pillars to your east.  Looking south you note with some trepidation how high you are above the cave floor, though you can get higher still on the second row of pillars, to your north.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  I  !\n ! III !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n=798, 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e=796, 	w="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=796, 	u=798, 	d=796},
{room=798,  	title="On the Singing Pillars - Bottom of Second Row", 	verbose="You are stood atop the lowest pillar of the second row, at the western end - the rest of the pillars climb to your east, while you can step down to the first row to your south. The third row of pillars towers high overhead, north of you.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n !  I  !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s=797, 	e=799, 	w="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=797, 	u=799, 	d=797},
{room=799,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="From here you can climb up to the next pillar on your east, or down to the pillar to your west. It\'s also possible to scramble down to the first row, south of here.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n !  I  !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s=796, 	e=800, 	w=798, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=798, 	u=800, 	d=796},
{room=800,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="The pillars both east and west of you are both lower than this one, the west one slightly more so. Generally the pillars rise to the east, where you can see them meet with the lowest pillar of the third row, still way above your head.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n !  I  !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e=801, 	w=799, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=799, 	u=801, 	d=799},
{room=801,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="About one third of the way up the second row of pillars, with the pillars on both sides being slightly higher than your current one, you can either follow the general line of ascent to the east, or go west.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n !  II !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=802, 	w=800, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=800, 	u=802, 	d=800},
{room=802,  	title="On the Singing Pillars - Halfway between Top and Bottom", 	verbose="This pillar marks the halfway point of the climb from the lowest pillar, visible below you to the southeast, to the highest pillar far above you to the northwest. To reach either one, you\'ll need to travel east to ascend, or west to descend.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n !  II !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="It\'s a long way down, and you don\'t feel suicidal.", 	e=803, 	w=801, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=801, 	u=803, 	d=801},
{room=803,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="Looking up, the third row of pillars appear unclimbably high to the north, but they slope down to the east where your current row slopes up to meet them. West, the pillars slope down towards the top of the pillars in the first row.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n !  II !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=804, 	w=802, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=802, 	u=804, 	d=802},
{room=804,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="Just one pillar seperates you and the highest pillar in the second row, and looking up and north you see you can almost climb up onto the third row from here. South, though, the drop onto the first row is enormous, and the drop to the floor below greater than that.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n ! III !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e=805, 	w=803, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=803, 	u=805, 	d=803},
{room=805,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="Here, on the penultimate pillar in the second row you can either scramble up to the third row, go east to reach the highest pillar of this row, or descend to the west where the first row rises to meet this one.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n ! III !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n="You fetch up against the smooth, hard surface of a pillar.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=806, 	w=804, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=804, 	u=808, 	d=804},
{room=806,  	title="On the Singing Pillars - Top of Second Row", 	verbose="Here, on the highest, more easterly pillar of the second row you can easily step up onto the lowest pillar of the third row to the north, or decend via the pillars sloping down to the west.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n !  II !\n ! III !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n=807, 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	w=805, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=805, 	u=807, 	d=805},
{room=807,  	title="On the Singing Pillars - Bottom of Third Row", 	verbose="Immediately south of you is the step down from this, the lowest of the pillars in the third row, onto the second row. North and east is nothing but solid, black, glassy rock, while to the west pillars ascend towards the roof of the cave.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n !  I  !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="There\'s a VERY solid rock face barring your way.", 	s=806, 	e="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	w=808, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=806, 	u=808, 	d=806},
{room=808,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="It\'s just possible to go south from here, down onto the second row, but easier by far to ascend to the pillar to your west or climb down to the one on your east.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n !  I  !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n="There\'s a VERY solid rock face barring your way.", 	s=805, 	e=807, 	w=809, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=807, 	u=809, 	d=805},
{room=809,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="The highest pillar of the lowest triplet of the third row, the pillars to both east and west of you are slightly lower, though generally the pillars slope up to the west.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n !  I  !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n="There\'s a VERY solid rock face barring your way.", 	s="It\'s a long way down, and you don\'t feel suicidal.", 	e=808, 	w=810, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=808, 	u=810, 	d=808},
{room=810,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="South the scene is mercifully screened by darkness, else vertigo would surely overwhelm you and send you plunging down to your death.  You can climb still higher via the pillars to your west, or lower by travelling to the east.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n !  II !\n !  I  !\n +-----+ ", 	n="There\'s a VERY solid rock face barring your way.", 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e=809, 	w=811, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=809, 	u=811, 	d=809},
{room=811,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="The pillars continue to ascend to the west and descend to the east.  Looking up and to the north, you can just make out the top of the sheer rock face the pillars grow up against.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n !  II !\n !  II !\n +-----+ ", 	n="There\'s a VERY solid rock face barring your way.", 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e=810, 	w=812, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=810, 	u=812, 	d=810},
{room=812,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="The pillars to both east and west of you are lower than the one you are currently on, though the general trend for the pillars in this row is to rise to the west and fall to the east, where they offer a means of climbing down onto the row below.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n !  II !\n ! III !\n +-----+ ", 	n="There\'s a VERY solid rock face barring your way.", 	s="The fall would kill you.", 	e=811, 	w=813, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=811, 	u=813, 	d=811},
{room=813,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="Although the pillars to both east and west of you are above this one, you can see where the pillars rising to the west reach the very top of the rock face you are scaling by means of the pillars. Looking up, the top of the rock face is almost within reach.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n ! III !\n !  I  !\n +-----+", 	n="There\'s a VERY solid rock face barring your way.", 	s="It\'s a long way down, and you don\'t feel suicidal.", 	e=812, 	w=814, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=812, 	u=814, 	d=812},
{room=814,  	title="On the Singing Pillars", 	verbose="This, the penultimate pillar of the three rows, offers simple choices - clamber onto the top of the rock face to the north, stand atop the highest pillar to the west, descend to the east or...well, leaving to the south would not be wise.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n ! III !\n !  II !\n +-----+", 	n=816, 	s="Walking on air isn\'t amongst your many talents.", 	e=813, 	w=815, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=813, 	u=816, 	d=813},
{room=815,  	title="On the Singing Pillars - The Topmost Pillar.", 	verbose="The pillar underneath your feet emits a low booming note, mingling with the other tones and vibrating up through your feet, tempting you to step up onto the top of the rock face to your north. Beyond that, you can commence the long journey down by going east.\nAt your feet is a polished circle, glossier than the rest of the pillar surface, and inside is an inscription that looks like this:\n +-----+\n ! III !\n ! III !\n ! III !\n +-----+", 	n=816, 	s="It\'s a long way down, and you don\'t feel suicidal.", 	e=814, 	w="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=814, 	u=816, 	d=814},
{room=816,  	title="Top of Rock Face", 	verbose="Stood on a ledge above the highest of the singing pillars, you are close to the roof of the cavern, close enough to see individual drops of water beading and falling...looking to see where they might land induces immediate vertigo, the cavern being so incredibly high.  You can step down onto the highest of the pillars, to your south, or move north away from the edge, where the cavern roof slopes down to meet the ledge floor.", 	n=817, 	s=815, 	e="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	w="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=817, 	o=815, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d=815},
{room=817,  	title="Shrine above the Pillars", 	verbose="Here, at the back of the ledge, the ceiling has descended to a point where it almost brushes your head. In all directions bar south the roof curves down to meet the floor, giving the area a domed look, almost like the sort of place you\'d expect to find an altar.", 	n="If there was a way through there, you\'d have seen it.", 	s=816, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="The cave walls are black, glassy and VERY solid.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=816, 	u="The roof is so low there isn\'t an \"up\" available.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
