{room=861,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (1)", 	verbose="As you play Shades, you may come across a few boobytraps here and there which kill you off, for example dropping the wrong bomb. This sort of dying won\'t lose you any points (as long as you are careful) but you will of course lose any objects you\'ve managed to gather.  Apart from this sort of \"death\", there is the other sort which is when you get attacked and killed by either another player or one of the games own creatures, like the Guard and the Crow\n- More East, Info Centre West -", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=862, 	w=841, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=862, 	o=841, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=862,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (2)", 	verbose="If you get attacked you won\'t be able to move in the normal way, to run away you have to type FLEE <Direction>, for example FLEE NORTH or FL N for short. This\'ll stop the fight and get you out of trouble but you\'ll lose a few points into the bargain. Of course, you too can start a fight by typing KILL <Name> or KILL <Name> WITH <Weapon>, for example KILL BOB WITH AXE. If you\'ve got a weapon and you get get attacked, type RETaliate WITH <Weapon>, eg RET SWORD.\n- More East -", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=863, 	w=861, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=863, 	o=861, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=863,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (3)", 	verbose="After you\'ve been in a fight type SCORE and see how much STAMINA you have left, this goes down every time you are hit in a fight and if it reachs zero you have been killed, so it\'s a good idea to keep it topped up to the amount shown by MAX STAMINA on your score. Hint: One way to top up your stamina is to touch the Strange Little Girl.\n- More East -", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=864, 	w=862, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=864, 	o=862, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=864,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (4)", 	verbose="Don\'t expect to win your first few fights, your opponent will almost certainly be stronger and more experienced than you. But with practice you\'ll find yourself acquiring the skills needed to teach an aggressor a lesson and will be better able to defend yourself.  Don\'t go about attacking anything that moves though, that tends to make you unpopular and means others will gang up on you.\n- More East -", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=865, 	w=863, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=865, 	o=863, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=865,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (5)", 	verbose="One important factor in fighting is your level - the higher your level the faster you throw blows during a fight and hence the more damage you do to your opponent. If you should be killed, the number of points depends on a number of factors - go South from here to see a summary of these.\n- More East -", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s=869, 	e=866, 	w=864, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=866, 	o=864, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=866,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (6)", 	verbose="PLEASE IGNORE THE FOLLOWING.\nPACIFISM IS NO MORE! For those who don\'t like fighting and don\'t like losing points by fleeing, there is the option of pacifism. When you first create your persona it is a \"fighter\" - if you want to you can make it a pacifist which means you will lose no points for fleeing although you can still be killed (when you will lose points). Treasure is only worth half as much to a pacifist though, so you should think carefully before choosing this option.\n- More East -", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=867, 	w=865, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=867, 	o=865, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=867,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (7)", 	verbose="It will take considerable practice and experience to master the methods of fighting and escaping with your life - in fact this is one of the most important aspects to the game, so the better you learn it the more successful you are likely to be.\n- West to read back, OUT for Information Centre -", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w=866, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=841, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=868,  	title="Life and Death in the Shade (8) *Reserved*", 	verbose="Spare Room", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=869,  	title="Points lost through being killed", 	verbose="The rules for points loss if you are killed are quite simple: If you get into a fight and lose, you will lose a fraction which dependent on your level. This goes from a maximum of half your score at Sorcerer to 1/32nd Adventurer. However, if you started the fight you will lose twice as much. If you attack and kill someone you get 1/8th of the points they lose, if they attack you and lose you get 1/4 of what they lose.\n-- Exit North --", 	n=865, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=865, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=870,  	title="Scripting Rules", 	verbose="THE FOLLOWING RULES APPLY TO SCRIPTING\n\nScripting is described as using functions of your software to allow you to \'play\' the game without actually playing the game. I wont go into more detail cos those that know how to do it, know what it is.\nThis information is directed at YOU\n\nMORE NORTH", 	n=880, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=841, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way. "},
{room=871,  	title="Instructions (1)", 	verbose="The aim of the game is quite simple, to score points by collecting the treasure scattered about the land and dropping it in the Mad Kings room. You move about by typing simple english commands like GO NORTH or just NORTH or even N, and you collect and drop objects by using GET and DROP respectively. You can also cast various spells of which the most useful is undoubtedly the WHERE spell, as in WHERE IS THE TREASURE (you can abbreviate this to WH T).\n- More South -", 	n=841, 	s=872, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	nw="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	se="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	sw="Walking through walls was never your strong point", 	i=872, 	o=841, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=872,  	title="Instructions (2)", 	verbose="Try typing WH T a few times now - you may find it doesn\'t work too well, this is because the lower your score the less spell-casting ability you have. If you persist though it will work eventually and list all the places where there is treasure. You\'ll need to spend time exploring before you get to know your way about, because other people will be trying to beat you to the treasure.\n- More South -", 	n=871, 	s=873, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=873, 	o=871, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=873,  	title="Instructions (3)", 	verbose="During the course of play you\'ll come across puzzles put there to make life that little bit more difficult - a number of these puzzles require two players to solve them so it helps to make some friends, especially as other players are the best source of help with the game. To talk to other players in the same room as you, type SAY then your message, for example if you type SAY HI, can you help me please? others in the room will see \"<Yourname> says \"Hi, can you help me please?\".\n- More South -", 	n=872, 	s=874, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=874, 	o=872, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=874,  	title="Instructions (4)", 	verbose="If there are no other players in the same room as you (type LOOK or GLANCE to see who there is) you can always SHOUT your message which is just like SAY except everyone in the game hears you. For example, if you are stuck you could SHOUT HELP, I\'M NEW HERE! and everyone in the game would see <Yourname> shouts \"HELP, I\'M NEW HERE!\". You can always type WHO to see who is currently playing.\n- More South -", 	n=873, 	s=875, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=875, 	o=873, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=875,  	title="Instructions (5)", 	verbose="A third way of talking to other players (besides SAY and SHOUT) is TELL, which operates just like telepathy. Only the person you tell your message to will hear it, so for example if you type WHO and see that someone called MERLIN is playing you could type TELL MERLIN HI, COULD YOU TELL ME THE WAY TO THE MAD KING PLEASE? and Merlin will see <Yourname> tells you \"HI, COULD YOU TELL ME THE WAY TO THE MAD KING PLEASE?\". You can use TELL to another player from anywhere in the game.\n- More South -", 	n=874, 	s=876, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=876, 	o=874, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=876,  	title="Instructions (6)", 	verbose="It will take you a while to get used to the layout and to the way you deal with other players, but once you have you\'ll find yourself scoring points with ease. The very best players will eventually reach the level of Wizard or Witch, where you become Immortal and are granted fabulous powers over the land and all its inhabitants. If you type LEVELS you\'ll get information on how many points you need to make to progress through the levels before you reach Wizard/Witch.\n- More South -", 	n=875, 	s=877, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=877, 	o=875, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=877,  	title="Instructions (7)", 	verbose="Once you begin to get a picture of the Lands layout (and we suggest you draw a map) you can type BRIEF to stop the long description being displayed every time you enter a room. After you\'ve typed BRIEF you can always type VERBOSE to get the long descriptions back, or you can LOOK which always displays the full description.\nFinally, try typing COMMANDS to get a short list of some of the more useful commands, also try typing HELP.\n- Go Out for the Info Centre, or North to read backwards -", 	n=876, 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=841, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=878,  	title="Inside Recycling Machine", 	verbose="Somehow, you manage to squeeze between the razor sharp blades of the Recycling machine and find yourself in a dark void with no visible exits.  It would be suicide for you to attempt to return the way you came so you decide to sit here and contemplate the meaning of life", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw=881, 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=879,  	title="Scripting rules continued", 	verbose="A player who is suspected of using a hoover script will in the first instance be warned by an Arch (whom will hopefully will have had it brought to his/her) attention by another player)l A further breach of this rule will result in a final warning If this warning isnt heeded to, then the said player will have his entire ACCOUNT osctrasised to game 8 Any personna that has been ostracised WILL NOT be allowed to make immortal.\nGo OUT", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=841, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=880,  	title="Scripting rules continued", 	verbose="The rule is as follows: - Anyone who is found to be using a script to collect T will be ostracised to game 8 so that they can script away to their hearts content.  By scripting I dont mean using a small one to do the west tower or whatever, but a full script to hoover the game Fighting scripts ARE NOT included in this offer cos every fighter uses a script in one way or another.\n\nMORE NORTH", 	n=879, 	s=870, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
