{room=890,  	title="Under the hidden trapdoor", 	verbose="Lifting the heavy trapdoor, you venture down a steep flight of worn stone steps into inky darkness. Cobwebs brush your groping hands and caress your face. There is a musty smell in the air and you feel sure this cannot be the pub\'s cellar. You have stumbled into somewhere that no human (or indeed any other form of) being has visited for years. There is the sound of trickling water and placing your ear to a damp rock wall, you hear a deep distant roar.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se=891, 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u=581, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
