{room=894,  	title="The Confessional", 	verbose="You have entered a tiny niche, which seems to have been hewn from the living rock for a purpose. There is a hassock here and you notice a little grill set in the back of the niche.  Peering more closely, you can just make out a flickering light behind the grill, and applying your eye to it, you make out the grizzled features of an old priest, who seems to be asleep. A notice in front of you reads, in an uncial script, \"CONFESS YOUR SINS HERE AND BE CLEANSED\".", 	n=895, 	s=893, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=895, 	o=893, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
