{room=971,  	title="Outside the \"Bag and Brick\" pub", 	verbose="You are at the entrance of the Bag and Brick, an area reserved for peaceful chatting, meeting friends for a drink and generally relaxing while accepting large bribes from certain corrupt officials. To the south is a door labelled \"The Olde Public Bar\", to the east is a dark door labelled \"The Den\" and to the north is a narrow alleyway. Above you hangs a complex scoreboard of some kind, and looking at the walls just makes you cross-eyed.", 	n=584, 	s=582, 	e=583, 	w=580, 	ne=890, 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=583, 	o=580, 	u=1070, 	d=581},
{room=972,  	title="Inside the wicker man", 	verbose="You awaken from an uneasy sleep with your head pounding and a sticky, bitter taste in your mouth. You can hear the noise of frightened animals and manage to struggle to your feet. After the first moments of dizziness pass you find yourself high above the ground, looking out into a forest, standing on a wooden platform. Around you, separated by wooden bars are frightened animals together with a few men who huddle together silently, looking out at the sun rising over the trees. You can smell smoke...", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=973,  	title="Dementia\'s Home for the Criminally Insane.", 	verbose="You have entered a room, blinding in its whiteness. The walls are white, the floor is white, and there is an iron bed in the corner made up with very uncomfortable, cheap looking sheets. More disturbingly, a worn straitjacket lies on the bed, attached with iron manacles.  There is a bedside table, cluttered with pill bottles, and a glass containing a worn pair of false teeth. You feel disquietened, as if you have viewed the jumble that is Dementia\'s mind....", 	n=581, 	s=983, 	e=583, 	w=583, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw=320, 	se=971, 	sw=228, 	i=491, 	o=559, 	u=575, 	d=553},
{room=974,  	title="In the large round bed.", 	verbose="The large round bed seems to extend almost for ever. Covered with brilliant white coverings that radiate comfort, you know this is a happy place to be.  Looking closely at the coverings you notice a coat of arms featuring an upturned horseshoe and empty bottle of smirnov surrounded by weapons of war.  Just beyond the edge of the bed you can just make out the rest of a large room.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o=976, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=975,  	title="A cave on the Island of Delos", 	verbose="You are stood in a large cave. Behind you crashes the ocean, where dolphins leap and frolic. A deer is grazing to your left, and above your head, crows swoop and dive amongst the ravenous vultures.  You are perturbed by the wolf to your right, which sits staring at you, and licking its chops. Further into the cave, you can see the entrance to the stable area, and a brief glimpse of white feathers and gold. You can hear the soft sounds of a stringed instrument.", 	n=320, 	s=581, 	e=980, 	w=419, 	ne=985, 	nw=986, 	se=999, 	sw=1013, 	i=1042, 	o=581, 	u=1034, 	d=1060},
{room=976,  	title="The master bedroom", 	verbose="The room is large and impressive, much of the floor space is devoted to a huge bed resplendent in fine white covers.  The walls are adorned with a number of trophies in the form of scalps.  A huge fire burns in the ancient fireplace and above it there is a large coat of arms, again depicting an upturned horseshoe and emptied Smirnov bottle.  A bar can be found in the corner. All the optics appear to be Vodka.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=974, 	o=978, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=977,  	title="Tajemstvi\'s Secret HideAway", 	verbose="As You enter you feel faint and slip to the floor!!  Moments later you re-awaken on a beautiful desert island the pure white beach is highlighted by the moonlight, and the stars are relected in the still lagoon a few steps away. The palm trees sway slighty in the warm night breeze. You notice a small fire further down the beach, as you approach it you see taj sat on the shore.  you reach out to touch her but she vanishes into thin air....  You realise you were dreaming and are in an empty room", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=978,  	title="The entrance hall.", 	verbose="A huge open fire adorns the north wall of this room.  Swords, axes and other weapons of war are attached to the walls. Some of them deliberately, some of the impaled in the wall as a result of some fight or another.  The benches scattered around the room are generously laid out with various ales, beers, wines and of course Vodka.  A well guarded small looking door is concealed in the West wall.  A huge wooden door can be found opposite the hearth.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s=984, 	e="You can\'t go that way.", 	w=976, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i=976, 	o=984, 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=979,  	title="The Runway", 	verbose="All around you the land is entirely flat.  A vast, straight, concrete runway stretches off ahead of you.  There are little flashing lights down either side of the runway.  The roar of jet engines surrounds you.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=1, 	w="You can\'t go that way.", 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=980,  	title="The Locksmith\'s Workshop", 	verbose="All around are all manner of doors, cupboards, clocks and fasteners and other things which have locks, even on the floor and ceiling.  There are twelve which look slightly different to all the others and appear to need a unique Key to unlock them.  Fortunately, after you test a couple, you find Someone has done this already.  One thing you do notice is that some of the doors have a reddish glow, as if warning you about going through them.", 	n=439, 	s=130, 	e=581, 	w=983, 	ne=402, 	nw=8, 	se=200, 	sw=228, 	i=1, 	o=580, 	u=559, 	d=279},
{room=981,  	title="The Boudoir", 	verbose="thElsie si redecorating\nThe floor is covered with discarded shoes.  There are far too many red stilletos and patterned stockings lie everywher A magnificent dressing table with a hollywood-style lit mirror dominates the west wall. A huge array of make-up lies on the table.", 	n="You can\'t go that way.", 	s="You can\'t go that way.", 	e=581, 	w=6, 	ne="You can\'t go that way.", 	nw="You can\'t go that way.", 	se="You can\'t go that way.", 	sw="You can\'t go that way.", 	i="You can\'t go that way.", 	o="You can\'t go that way.", 	u="You can\'t go that way.", 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=982,  	title="Motley\'s Twopit Room", 	verbose="You are at the east end of the Twopit Room. The floor here is littered with thin rock slabs, which make it easy to descend the pits. There is a path here bypassing the pits to connect passages from east and west. There are holes all over, but the only big one is on the wall directly over the west pit where you can\'t get to it.\n...Uh, wrong game...", 	n=581, 	s=53, 	e=559, 	w=150, 	ne=401, 	nw=772, 	se=817, 	sw=261, 	i=488, 	o=439, 	u=583, 	d="You can\'t go that way."},
{room=983,  	title="Mischief\'s Off Licence", 	verbose="You arrive in a room lined with shelves, each shelf containing bottle after bottle of vodka. Every conceivable brand you can think of is here, as well as quite a few you hadn\'t! Dotted around on the shelves are a few of Mischief\'s keepsakes, and at one end of the room sit some extremely comfortable chairs gathered around an open blazing fireplace. This is a room to rest and relax in, and you instantly feel at ease. You sit in one of the chairs, and a filled vodka glass appears.Someone chuckles. ", 	n=581, 	s=974, 	e=980, 	w=583, 	ne=1040, 	nw=971, 	se=1006, 	sw=228, 	i=990, 	o=559, 	u=973, 	d=553},
